1
00:00:01,234 --> 00:00:02,635
Hold on.

2
00:00:05,005 --> 00:00:07,007
[Closing Day Of Bonjour Bakery]
Don't eat this just yet.

3
00:00:07,007 --> 00:00:08,675
- Okay.
- Hold on.

4
00:00:08,675 --> 00:00:09,810
Just wait.

5
00:00:09,810 --> 00:00:12,579
Don't eat this just yet.

6
00:00:12,579 --> 00:00:14,547
I'll explain in a bit.

7
00:00:15,048 --> 00:00:16,817
Here you go, ma'am. Don't eat it just yet.

8
00:00:16,817 --> 00:00:19,119
- Okay?
- All right, I won't.

9
00:00:19,119 --> 00:00:20,720
Don't eat it yet.

10
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:23,523
Sorry, can I have
your attention for a second?

11
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:25,459
You know the bread I just gave you?

12
00:00:25,459 --> 00:00:27,160
The bread with the crown.

13
00:00:27,160 --> 00:00:28,595
It's called a galette des rois,

14
00:00:28,595 --> 00:00:30,564
and they eat it in France every January,

15
00:00:30,564 --> 00:00:34,067
just like we eat tteokguk
on New Year's Day.

16
00:00:34,067 --> 00:00:38,271
A porcelain figurine is often
placed inside the bread.

17
00:00:38,271 --> 00:00:40,340
But since we couldn't do that,

18
00:00:40,340 --> 00:00:42,676
we put a chestnut in one of the five...

19
00:00:42,676 --> 00:00:45,045
Sir. Ma'am. Don't eat it yet.

20
00:00:45,045 --> 00:00:46,513
When I count to three...

21
00:00:46,513 --> 00:00:48,248
Wait a minute. Ma'am, please.

22
00:00:48,248 --> 00:00:50,450
Sir, stop. Hold on.

23
00:00:51,318 --> 00:00:53,386
Don't eat it now. Just wait a bit.

24
00:00:53,386 --> 00:00:56,790
When I count to three,

25
00:00:56,790 --> 00:00:59,359
cut the bread with your knife.

26
00:00:59,359 --> 00:01:00,494
Don't do it yet.

27
00:01:00,494 --> 00:01:01,995
One.

28
00:01:01,995 --> 00:01:03,396
Two.

29
00:01:04,164 --> 00:01:05,899
Three! Go on.

30
00:01:07,801 --> 00:01:09,169
All right.

31
00:01:09,169 --> 00:01:10,437
If you find a chestnut,

32
00:01:10,437 --> 00:01:12,806
- make sure to let me know.
- Should we cut it?

33
00:01:12,806 --> 00:01:14,140
Yes, try cutting it.

34
00:01:14,140 --> 00:01:16,409
The chestnut is about this size.

35
00:01:16,409 --> 00:01:17,577
I got one!

36
00:01:17,577 --> 00:01:19,145
- You got a chestnut?
- Oh, my.

37
00:01:22,883 --> 00:01:25,018
All right, then. In that case...

38
00:01:26,086 --> 00:01:30,090
- This flower is a gift for you.
- Thank you.

39
00:01:30,090 --> 00:01:33,326
- Let me crown you.
- All right.

40
00:01:33,326 --> 00:01:36,530
- Who got the chestnut?
- This lady over here.

41
00:01:36,530 --> 00:01:39,399
Whoever got the chestnut
should sing a song!

42
00:01:41,501 --> 00:01:44,271
I'll sing for you if you want.
Just tell me the title.

43
00:01:44,271 --> 00:01:46,839
I'll do it since I got the chestnut.

44
00:01:48,708 --> 00:01:51,044
Here is your microphone, ma'am.

45
00:01:51,044 --> 00:01:54,881
- Here's your microphone.
- Here's your mic.

46
00:01:59,786 --> 00:02:04,328
♪ Even when the pain is unbearable ♪

47
00:02:04,328 --> 00:02:05,959
[A Woman's Life By Lee Mi Ja]

48
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:11,665
- ♪ Even when my heart breaks ♪
- ♪ Heart breaks ♪

49
00:02:11,665 --> 00:02:15,035
♪ I have to bear the unimaginable sorrow ♪

50
00:02:15,035 --> 00:02:19,106
♪ All on my own ♪

51
00:02:19,106 --> 00:02:23,043
♪ As I stumble through ♪

52
00:02:23,043 --> 00:02:28,423
♪ This hard journey of life ♪

53
00:02:42,028 --> 00:02:45,647
[In This Relentless Life
Where It's Hard To Catch A Breath]

54
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:50,737
[If We Can Share With One Another]

55
00:02:50,737 --> 00:02:54,260
[The Lingering Sweetness Of A Slice Of Dessert]

56
00:02:56,476 --> 00:03:01,980
[We Can Create A Moment Of Sweet Comfort]

57
00:03:03,316 --> 00:03:05,485
[Bonjour Bakery]

58
00:03:05,485 --> 00:03:08,121
[We Gifted The Courage
To Overcome Hesitation]

59
00:03:08,121 --> 00:03:09,923
- Hello.
- Welcome.

60
00:03:09,923 --> 00:03:12,658
Come on in. Take a seat over there.

61
00:03:16,229 --> 00:03:21,316
[And We Were Gifted In Return
By A Season We Could Never Forget]

62
00:03:23,136 --> 00:03:25,572
[A Place Where Everyone]

63
00:03:25,572 --> 00:03:30,060
[Could Rest A While With
Rising Excitement In Their Hearts]

64
00:03:34,481 --> 00:03:39,492
[A One-Of-A-Kind Senior Cafe]

65
00:03:44,090 --> 00:03:51,511
[Bonjour Bakery]

66
00:04:00,143 --> 00:04:01,675
[Senior Cafe]
[Bonjour Bakery]

67
00:04:01,675 --> 00:04:05,645
[Bonjour Bakery]

68
00:04:05,645 --> 00:04:09,434
[Hannam-Dong, Seoul]

69
00:04:10,216 --> 00:04:11,317
Have they arrived?

70
00:04:11,317 --> 00:04:13,119
Here they are.

71
00:04:13,653 --> 00:04:15,021
[Main Chef Cha Seung Won]

72
00:04:15,021 --> 00:04:16,690
Hello, Hee Ae.

73
00:04:16,690 --> 00:04:18,224
[Sous Chef Lee Ki Taek]
Gosh.

74
00:04:18,224 --> 00:04:19,459
Hello.

75
00:04:19,459 --> 00:04:21,361
- Welcome.
- Hello.

76
00:04:21,361 --> 00:04:23,897
- Hello, Hee Ae.
- You look so stylish.

77
00:04:23,897 --> 00:04:25,365
Come on in.

78
00:04:25,365 --> 00:04:27,500
- Hello.
- Hello.

79
00:04:28,068 --> 00:04:29,635
- Hello.
- Hello.

80
00:04:30,403 --> 00:04:32,072
[Barista Kim Seon Ho]
Hello.

81
00:04:32,072 --> 00:04:33,805
- Hello.
- Hi.

82
00:04:33,805 --> 00:04:34,841
What is that?

83
00:04:34,841 --> 00:04:38,745
These are coffee and ade drinks.

84
00:04:38,745 --> 00:04:40,146
- We made them.
- Really?

85
00:04:40,146 --> 00:04:41,681
It's for you to taste.

86
00:04:41,681 --> 00:04:43,416
You made this, Hee Ae?

87
00:04:43,983 --> 00:04:45,685
We just learned them during café training.

88
00:04:45,685 --> 00:04:47,020
- Really?
- Yes.

89
00:04:47,020 --> 00:04:48,655
- Come this way.
- Okay.

90
00:04:48,655 --> 00:04:51,991
[First Meeting Before The Opening]

91
00:04:51,991 --> 00:04:54,294
- Can we drink this?
- This is lemon tea.

92
00:04:54,294 --> 00:04:55,662
- Would you like coffee?
- I want coffee.

93
00:04:55,662 --> 00:04:57,831
It's an iced Americano and a latte.

94
00:04:57,831 --> 00:04:59,532
- I'll have the iced Americano.
- Iced Americano?

95
00:04:59,532 --> 00:05:00,600
[Hee Ae And Seung Won]

96
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:02,535
[11 Years In The Same Agency
First Joint Media Appearance]

97
00:05:02,535 --> 00:05:04,104
- What about you, Ki Taek?
- I'll have the same.

98
00:05:04,104 --> 00:05:06,306
- Anything works for me.
- This one's a latte.

99
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:07,874
- The ade is...
- The ade is really tasty.

100
00:05:07,874 --> 00:05:09,209
I'll take whatever's left.

101
00:05:09,209 --> 00:05:11,444
- No, have what you want.
- We've already had some. You can choose.

102
00:05:11,444 --> 00:05:12,846
- That's grapefruit ade.
- I'll have the ade.

103
00:05:12,846 --> 00:05:14,414
Okay.

104
00:05:14,414 --> 00:05:17,317
The two of you have never
done a show together before, right?

105
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:18,852
- No, never.
- That's right.

106
00:05:18,852 --> 00:05:19,886
First time working together.

107
00:05:19,886 --> 00:05:23,022
- You've been at the same agency forever.
- Yes.

108
00:05:23,022 --> 00:05:24,891
- But we never run into each other.
- Hardly ever.

109
00:05:24,891 --> 00:05:27,093
- There's not much chance.
- We're both so busy.

110
00:05:27,093 --> 00:05:29,963
- That's true.
- And Seung Won's a bit...

111
00:05:29,963 --> 00:05:33,633
I think he said something about
not wanting to get close to people.

112
00:05:33,633 --> 00:05:37,770
But to be honest,
I really relate to that.

113
00:05:38,238 --> 00:05:41,941
Was it that I keep people at a distance?

114
00:05:41,941 --> 00:05:44,310
Yes, I can relate to that.

115
00:05:44,310 --> 00:05:46,646
Or did I misunderstand?

116
00:05:46,646 --> 00:05:47,881
[Who Is She Asking?]

117
00:05:47,881 --> 00:05:49,783
- Yes, ask him.
- No, that's not it.

118
00:05:49,783 --> 00:05:54,287
I just meant that when it comes
to people I'm not connected to,

119
00:05:54,287 --> 00:05:55,955
I don't go out of my way
to be overly nice to them.

120
00:05:55,955 --> 00:05:58,892
I'm just not that kind of person.

121
00:05:58,892 --> 00:06:00,293
I also feel like...

122
00:06:00,293 --> 00:06:02,162
- I think she's similar to me.
- Yes.

123
00:06:02,162 --> 00:06:03,730
I am the same way.

124
00:06:03,730 --> 00:06:05,498
If I bump into someone,
I'm happy to see them,

125
00:06:05,498 --> 00:06:08,100
and I root for them from a distance.

126
00:06:09,002 --> 00:06:11,805
But it doesn't go much further than that.

127
00:06:11,805 --> 00:06:12,872
Yes, exactly.

128
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:14,474
That's how I am.

129
00:06:14,474 --> 00:06:15,542
Right? And in a way,

130
00:06:15,542 --> 00:06:18,378
that might be the most
solid kind of relationship.

131
00:06:18,378 --> 00:06:22,181
Relationships like that last longest.

132
00:06:22,682 --> 00:06:24,951
By the way, will there be many customers?

133
00:06:24,951 --> 00:06:26,352
We honestly have no idea.

134
00:06:26,352 --> 00:06:27,987
We don't know if there will be
many or few customers.

135
00:06:27,987 --> 00:06:30,790
The locals are really curious and excited.

136
00:06:30,790 --> 00:06:33,760
They come by daily
to the construction site

137
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:35,294
to see if the café is open yet.

138
00:06:41,935 --> 00:06:45,705
[At The Foot Of Bangjang Mountain
In Gochang-Gun]

139
00:06:45,705 --> 00:06:49,846
[There Is A Small Village]

140
00:06:54,347 --> 00:06:55,915
[There Are 81 Households]

141
00:06:55,915 --> 00:06:59,086
[Most Residents Are Over 65 Years Old]

142
00:06:59,086 --> 00:07:02,736
[In This Quiet Neighborhood]

143
00:07:05,525 --> 00:07:08,428
[The Village Corner Store]

144
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:12,231
[That Closed Down A Long Time Ago]

145
00:07:13,299 --> 00:07:15,401
[Was Turned Into A Local Bakery]

146
00:07:15,401 --> 00:07:21,140
[And Its Doors Were Reopened]

147
00:07:21,140 --> 00:07:22,675
Old people like us can't eat out much

148
00:07:22,675 --> 00:07:24,744
since it's hard to get around.

149
00:07:24,744 --> 00:07:26,979
- You can't go out very far.
- That's right.

150
00:07:28,047 --> 00:07:30,316
We have a car,

151
00:07:30,316 --> 00:07:32,518
so we used to go out a lot,

152
00:07:32,518 --> 00:07:35,755
but my husband is
getting quite old now, so...

153
00:07:35,755 --> 00:07:38,024
- So, you don't anymore?
- We can't.

154
00:07:38,024 --> 00:07:41,027
I've only bought stuff to eat at home.

155
00:07:41,027 --> 00:07:42,595
Since I'm not young anymore,

156
00:07:42,595 --> 00:07:46,866
I've hardly ever spent time
in a big, fancy café.

157
00:07:46,866 --> 00:07:50,036
We wouldn't even know where to start.

158
00:07:50,036 --> 00:07:52,872
We might pick up some bread at the store,

159
00:07:52,872 --> 00:07:55,441
but we don't know
about fancy pastries and stuff.

160
00:07:55,441 --> 00:07:57,210
We only eat rice.

161
00:07:57,210 --> 00:08:00,446
Just the fact that a space
is being created just for seniors

162
00:08:00,446 --> 00:08:01,881
is a really nice idea.

163
00:08:01,881 --> 00:08:04,217
After all, there are a lot of places
for younger people to go

164
00:08:04,217 --> 00:08:07,153
all over the city.

165
00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:09,088
[That's Why We Created]

166
00:08:09,088 --> 00:08:14,027
[Bonjour Bakery]

167
00:08:14,027 --> 00:08:16,195
- Hello.
- Hello.

168
00:08:17,497 --> 00:08:19,332
[Just For Seniors Over 65 Years Old]
Hello.

169
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:21,634
[And Their Acquaintances]
Welcome, how many people?

170
00:08:21,634 --> 00:08:23,703
- Hello, welcome back.
- You're regulars, right?

171
00:08:23,703 --> 00:08:25,137
Come this way.

172
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:35,581
[Full Of Flavors]
[That Are Strangely Familiar]

173
00:08:35,581 --> 00:08:39,518
[To The Local Senior Residents]

174
00:08:42,555 --> 00:08:46,526
[Filled With Gochang's
Locally Grown Ingredients]

175
00:08:46,526 --> 00:08:51,263
[The French Dessert Café]
[Bonjour Bakery]

176
00:08:54,801 --> 00:08:56,836
- We loved it.
- It was so tasty.

177
00:08:56,836 --> 00:08:58,404
[Just Maybe]

178
00:08:58,404 --> 00:09:00,239
Thank you for these desserts.

179
00:09:00,873 --> 00:09:02,976
[Bread]
[Bonjour Bakery]

180
00:09:02,976 --> 00:09:04,944
[It Could Be A Sweet Resting Place]

181
00:09:04,944 --> 00:09:10,916
[For The Senior Locals]

182
00:09:13,519 --> 00:09:16,522
Apparently, we need to memorize

183
00:09:16,522 --> 00:09:18,424
- the dessert descriptions.
- The names are tricky.

184
00:09:18,424 --> 00:09:20,626
- They are.
- I can't remember a single one.

185
00:09:20,626 --> 00:09:23,763
Perhaps we could print out small cards

186
00:09:23,763 --> 00:09:26,632
for the customers to take home
as a kind of souvenir.

187
00:09:26,632 --> 00:09:28,634
It can remind them of what they ate.

188
00:09:28,634 --> 00:09:30,903
- We could hand them out with dessert.
- That's a good idea.

189
00:09:30,903 --> 00:09:31,804
[We Can Make Dessert Cards]

190
00:09:31,804 --> 00:09:35,108
I've taken cards like that home myself.

191
00:09:35,108 --> 00:09:37,176
[Bonjour Cherry Blossom Tart]
They can see the explanation.

192
00:09:37,176 --> 00:09:38,511
[Bonjour Green Barley Field Tart]

193
00:09:38,511 --> 00:09:39,946
[The Nutty Green Barley Cream]
[Evokes The Green Barley Landscape]

194
00:09:39,946 --> 00:09:42,949
Did you know all the food on this menu

195
00:09:42,949 --> 00:09:44,751
was invented by this chef?

196
00:09:44,751 --> 00:09:47,353
- Really?
- They all taste amazing.

197
00:09:47,353 --> 00:09:50,289
I tried them all. They're all delicious.

198
00:09:50,289 --> 00:09:51,391
- Hello.
- Hello.

199
00:09:51,391 --> 00:09:53,225
This is our chef.

200
00:09:56,429 --> 00:09:57,997
When I'm in an unfamiliar space,

201
00:09:57,997 --> 00:10:00,733
and I have to study an unfamiliar manual,

202
00:10:00,733 --> 00:10:02,035
it's not that I don't want to do it,

203
00:10:02,035 --> 00:10:04,470
but since it never
even crossed my mind before,

204
00:10:04,470 --> 00:10:07,507
I get really stressed out by it.

205
00:10:07,507 --> 00:10:10,510
[Training Day One]

206
00:10:10,510 --> 00:10:12,245
[Chef Kwon Ju Won]
Check the temperature.

207
00:10:12,245 --> 00:10:14,047
[Owner Of Sous Le Gi]
It's still 62 degrees.

208
00:10:14,047 --> 00:10:15,181
[Creative Director Of Bonjour Bakery Menu]

209
00:10:15,181 --> 00:10:17,283
I think I'm really bad at this stuff.

210
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:18,785
- Machines.
- You're doing great.

211
00:10:18,785 --> 00:10:20,553
- I'm bad with machines.
- I see.

212
00:10:20,553 --> 00:10:22,321
It goes badly when I try things like this.

213
00:10:22,321 --> 00:10:24,724
Machines like this make me anxious.

214
00:10:24,724 --> 00:10:25,725
[Even The King Of Cooking]

215
00:10:25,725 --> 00:10:26,859
[Is Feeling The Pressure]
I get nervous

216
00:10:26,859 --> 00:10:28,361
since I'm so bad at handling them.

217
00:10:28,361 --> 00:10:30,963
I'll guide you through it.

218
00:10:34,868 --> 00:10:35,902
- How's that?
- A bit more.

219
00:10:35,902 --> 00:10:37,303
- More?
- Yes.

220
00:10:37,870 --> 00:10:38,938
This is hard.

221
00:10:38,938 --> 00:10:40,440
I didn't make it
thick enough at the start.

222
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,608
- But I'll try again.
- Yes.

223
00:10:49,849 --> 00:10:51,784
[Chef Lee So Yeong]
[Le Cordon Bleu Patisserie Diploma]

224
00:10:51,784 --> 00:10:53,719
[Sous Le Gui Sous Chef]

225
00:10:53,719 --> 00:10:55,855
[Here To Help Bonjour Bakery Run Smoothly]

226
00:11:05,631 --> 00:11:08,101
I think we need to fold it up to here

227
00:11:08,101 --> 00:11:11,470
for it to roll smoothly like this.

228
00:11:11,871 --> 00:11:15,775
[Hours Of Blood, Sweat, And Tears]

229
00:11:15,775 --> 00:11:19,555
[Painstaking Determination]

230
00:11:20,713 --> 00:11:22,315
- This just needs to be 30.
- Yes.

231
00:11:22,315 --> 00:11:24,617
And the rest depends on how it turns out.

232
00:11:24,617 --> 00:11:26,018
One, two, space.

233
00:11:26,018 --> 00:11:28,721
- One, two, one, two, then...
- That's right.

234
00:11:28,721 --> 00:11:29,989
- One, two, one, two.
- You got it.

235
00:11:29,989 --> 00:11:31,624
[He Succeeds Yet Again]
Okay.

236
00:11:31,624 --> 00:11:33,692
I'm so impressed.

237
00:11:36,662 --> 00:11:38,331
How fascinating.

238
00:11:38,331 --> 00:11:40,399
Seriously. That's crazy.

239
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:43,503
I'm the King of Baking.

240
00:11:43,503 --> 00:11:45,738
- So impressive.
- Seriously.

241
00:11:46,339 --> 00:11:48,407
[From Chef Cha]

242
00:11:48,407 --> 00:11:50,910
[To Chatissier]

243
00:11:50,910 --> 00:11:53,512
[An Amazing Evolution!]

244
00:11:56,349 --> 00:11:57,950
Do you want a straw?

245
00:11:57,950 --> 00:12:00,119
- No, thanks.
- You don't need one?

246
00:12:00,119 --> 00:12:02,187
- I don't want to break the camel's back.
- Okay.

247
00:12:02,688 --> 00:12:04,157
The last straw... Never mind.

248
00:12:04,157 --> 00:12:07,193
- The last straw? Oh, I get it.
- Forget it.

249
00:12:07,193 --> 00:12:08,761
[Chef Team In Action]
Jeez, this kid.

250
00:12:08,761 --> 00:12:10,363
- Is it too late?
- Unbelievable.

251
00:12:10,363 --> 00:12:11,531
Forget it.

252
00:12:11,531 --> 00:12:14,133
My joke went straight over his head.

253
00:12:15,067 --> 00:12:16,469
How's the baking going?

254
00:12:16,469 --> 00:12:17,670
Are you getting the hang of it?

255
00:12:17,670 --> 00:12:19,939
I heard you're very enthusiastic.

256
00:12:19,939 --> 00:12:21,574
He even offered to make us breakfast.

257
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:23,342
- Who did?
- Well, the thing is...

258
00:12:23,342 --> 00:12:25,612
- You're going to make us breakfast?
- Here's the thing...

259
00:12:25,612 --> 00:12:28,948
- I didn't mean I'd cook breakfast.
- Okay.

260
00:12:28,948 --> 00:12:31,884
- I heard Hee Ae likes Greek yogurt.
- That's right, I do.

261
00:12:31,884 --> 00:12:33,519
I was going to bring some,

262
00:12:33,519 --> 00:12:37,223
and maybe add some nuts and blueberries.
It was just a thought.

263
00:12:37,223 --> 00:12:38,858
[Majorly Disappointed]
That's not what I heard.

264
00:12:38,858 --> 00:12:39,959
- I heard he'd cook for us.
- No.

265
00:12:39,959 --> 00:12:42,528
- I was just going to-
- Greek yogurt for breakfast?

266
00:12:42,528 --> 00:12:43,863
- That's your breakfast, Hee Ae?
- Yes.

267
00:12:43,863 --> 00:12:46,232
- That's all you eat?
- Of course, not.

268
00:12:46,232 --> 00:12:48,267
I'll have it with some eggs,

269
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:49,835
some nuts, and so on.

270
00:12:49,835 --> 00:12:52,572
Then what will we do for lunch?

271
00:12:52,572 --> 00:12:56,275
I expect Seung Won
will whip up something good.

272
00:12:57,076 --> 00:12:59,212
- We know he has the skills.
- I...

273
00:12:59,212 --> 00:13:00,913
[Brief Excitement]
I'm too busy baking.

274
00:13:00,913 --> 00:13:02,081
[Followed By Disappointment]

275
00:13:02,081 --> 00:13:03,983
Every time I figure something out,

276
00:13:03,983 --> 00:13:06,852
I forget the thing that came before it.

277
00:13:06,852 --> 00:13:08,754
- I'll make you a detox juice.
- I'd love that.

278
00:13:08,754 --> 00:13:09,655
[Sales Pitch]
Give it a try.

279
00:13:09,655 --> 00:13:11,424
It doesn't taste great,
but it's good for your health.

280
00:13:11,424 --> 00:13:12,925
I'm happy to try anything.

281
00:13:12,925 --> 00:13:17,163
He's been mulling over this.

282
00:13:17,163 --> 00:13:18,631
But I mean... Yeah.

283
00:13:18,631 --> 00:13:21,067
[He Won't Let Up]
But when you eat Greek yogurt,

284
00:13:21,067 --> 00:13:23,736
what do you usually put in it?

285
00:13:24,937 --> 00:13:26,339
[Looking Forward To]
[Sweet Desserts For Seniors]

286
00:13:26,339 --> 00:13:29,891
[And Breakfast By Lee Ki Taek]

287
00:13:36,949 --> 00:13:40,386
[Bonjour Bakery Opening D-1]

288
00:13:42,121 --> 00:13:45,858
[Gapyeong-Ri, Sillim-Myeon,]
[Gochang-Gun, Jeollabuk-Do]

289
00:13:49,528 --> 00:13:50,429
What's this?

290
00:13:50,429 --> 00:13:53,232
I brought some blueberries and side dishes

291
00:13:53,232 --> 00:13:55,067
in this cooler bag.

292
00:13:55,067 --> 00:13:57,737
There's a wholesale market
right next to my neighborhood,

293
00:13:57,737 --> 00:13:59,839
and the tomatoes are especially tasty,

294
00:13:59,839 --> 00:14:01,440
so I went to buy some
the day before yesterday.

295
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:04,276
- You...
- Gosh, how thoughtful.

296
00:14:06,479 --> 00:14:08,814
- Just the fact that he brought them...
- Exactly.

297
00:14:08,814 --> 00:14:10,283
He really went out of his way.

298
00:14:10,283 --> 00:14:13,552
- He did.
- It was probably a lot of pressure.

299
00:14:13,552 --> 00:14:15,288
But this should be a one-off thing.

300
00:14:15,288 --> 00:14:17,223
- Don't go to such trouble again.
- She's right. Don't do it.

301
00:14:17,223 --> 00:14:19,025
We'll enjoy the benefits

302
00:14:19,025 --> 00:14:21,594
- just this once.
- Okay.

303
00:14:21,594 --> 00:14:22,728
All right.

304
00:14:22,728 --> 00:14:25,931
Who knows if we will truly benefit?

305
00:14:25,931 --> 00:14:28,434
It might end up tasting awful.

306
00:14:28,434 --> 00:14:30,803
We won't know until we taste it.

307
00:14:30,803 --> 00:14:34,173
But how can you go wrong with eggs?

308
00:14:34,173 --> 00:14:37,910
Some people are really bad
at cooking eggs.

309
00:14:37,910 --> 00:14:40,413
- "How can you cook an egg this badly?"
- "How can this..."

310
00:14:40,413 --> 00:14:42,915
"It just happened."

311
00:14:45,951 --> 00:14:47,453
- Is that it?
- It is.

312
00:14:47,453 --> 00:14:49,021
- Can I turn here?
- You can.

313
00:14:49,021 --> 00:14:51,190
- I can turn here?
- Yes, go ahead.

314
00:14:51,891 --> 00:14:53,292
This is the bakery.

315
00:14:53,292 --> 00:14:55,127
It's so pretty!

316
00:14:55,127 --> 00:14:57,129
This is the bakery shop.

317
00:14:58,297 --> 00:15:00,266
That's it. The one on the right.

318
00:15:00,266 --> 00:15:02,535
- Oh, goodness.
- Bonjour Bakery! It's so pretty.

319
00:15:02,535 --> 00:15:03,602
What do you think?

320
00:15:03,602 --> 00:15:05,771
How did they find this location?

321
00:15:05,771 --> 00:15:08,574
I think people will come from all over
once word gets out.

322
00:15:08,574 --> 00:15:11,177
- I think they definitely will.
- I think so.

323
00:15:11,177 --> 00:15:12,945
[Bonjour Bakery]

324
00:15:12,945 --> 00:15:14,443
[Welcome]
[To The Village Of Living Tradition]

325
00:15:19,884 --> 00:15:22,355
The view here is great.

326
00:15:22,355 --> 00:15:25,091
- The fields are so green.
- Let me help you with that.

327
00:15:25,091 --> 00:15:27,927
It's so charming and rustic.

328
00:15:27,927 --> 00:15:29,568
It's so pretty.

329
00:15:29,568 --> 00:15:32,816
[A Place Where The Green Barley Fields]
[Warm The Heart]

330
00:15:36,635 --> 00:15:40,149
