353
00:17:12,631 --> 00:17:14,132
It's very soft.

354
00:17:20,206 --> 00:17:23,209
It's a good hall for serving.

355
00:17:23,209 --> 00:17:25,044
I think it's not a bad layout.

356
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:26,378
Yes.

357
00:17:26,879 --> 00:17:28,447
They even have space for groups.

358
00:17:28,447 --> 00:17:30,316
- This section is...
- It's such a cute area.

359
00:17:30,316 --> 00:17:31,617
- It's a table for big groups.
- Yeah.

360
00:17:31,617 --> 00:17:33,319
You're right.

361
00:17:33,319 --> 00:17:36,889
These magnifying glasses
must be for the senior guests.

362
00:17:38,123 --> 00:17:40,392
That's what these are for.

363
00:17:44,565 --> 00:17:47,489
[For Seniors Who Need A Reading Aid]

364
00:17:48,167 --> 00:17:51,719
[We Prepared Magnifying Glasses]

365
00:17:53,472 --> 00:17:56,509
[Warm Towels]

366
00:17:56,509 --> 00:17:59,177
[And Cute Round Teacups]

367
00:18:04,517 --> 00:18:06,118
[Freshly Baked Goods]

368
00:18:06,118 --> 00:18:10,187
[Can Be Taken Home In Pretty Packages]

369
00:18:10,990 --> 00:18:12,791
- Where?
- This space is unreal.

370
00:18:12,791 --> 00:18:14,627
[Staff Break Room]

371
00:18:14,627 --> 00:18:16,295
This is the kitchen? No way.

372
00:18:16,295 --> 00:18:18,797
There's more through there.

373
00:18:23,035 --> 00:18:24,370
This is crazy.

374
00:18:24,370 --> 00:18:25,337
[Utility Kitchen]

375
00:18:25,337 --> 00:18:26,605
This is unbelievable.

376
00:18:26,605 --> 00:18:28,807
It's bigger and nicer than the hall.

377
00:18:28,807 --> 00:18:30,242
It even comes with this, Ki Taek.

378
00:18:30,242 --> 00:18:32,311
- Yes?
- Look what we have.

379
00:18:32,311 --> 00:18:34,547
- We got one!
- This thing here

380
00:18:34,547 --> 00:18:36,515
- rolls the dough flat
- Okay.

381
00:18:36,515 --> 00:18:37,516
So you can make the crust.

382
00:18:37,516 --> 00:18:40,085
- Oh, that's what it's for.
- Yes, that stuff.

383
00:18:40,085 --> 00:18:41,654
This kitchen's amazing!

384
00:18:41,654 --> 00:18:43,255
- It's huge.
- It's so impressive.

385
00:18:43,255 --> 00:18:45,958
- The ovens are big.
- They really went all out.

386
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:48,661
They furnished it exactly the same.

387
00:18:48,661 --> 00:18:50,629
This probably cost a lot.

388
00:18:50,629 --> 00:18:52,831
It's quite a pricey item.

389
00:18:55,601 --> 00:18:57,602
Look at all this setup.

390
00:18:58,037 --> 00:19:00,806
[Bread, Tart, Baked Goods]

391
00:19:00,806 --> 00:19:04,409
[A Space For Making
Special Daily Desserts For The Seniors]

392
00:19:05,778 --> 00:19:07,846
[There's No Room For A Single Mistake]

393
00:19:07,846 --> 00:19:11,744
[When It Comes]
[To The Intricate Work Of Baking]

394
00:19:16,190 --> 00:19:20,559
[A Kitchen That Feels Like A Laboratory]

395
00:19:20,559 --> 00:19:22,428
I think 80 degrees would do.

396
00:19:22,428 --> 00:19:24,129
It's 66 degrees.

397
00:19:24,129 --> 00:19:25,564
[Intense Focus With Perfect Precision]

398
00:19:25,564 --> 00:19:27,299
- How many grams was it?
- It was 42 grams.

399
00:19:27,299 --> 00:19:29,034
- Keep an eye on it.
- Okay.

400
00:19:31,403 --> 00:19:35,820
[After Hours Of Devoted Effort]

401
00:19:38,946 --> 00:19:43,283
[The Desserts Baked From The Heart]
[Are Fully Prepared]

402
00:19:47,853 --> 00:19:49,921
It's all here.

403
00:19:50,623 --> 00:19:52,625
- It's his notes on all the recipes.
- Yes.

404
00:19:52,625 --> 00:19:58,130
[The Dessert Recipes Seung Won Wrote Down
During His Training]

405
00:19:58,130 --> 00:20:00,566
So, here's how we should do this.

406
00:20:00,566 --> 00:20:01,634
First,

407
00:20:01,634 --> 00:20:04,970
let's plan what to make tomorrow,

408
00:20:04,970 --> 00:20:07,406
quickly get the ingredients ready,

409
00:20:07,406 --> 00:20:10,609
and then the two of you
can manage the hall out there

410
00:20:10,609 --> 00:20:13,012
and prepare the coffee and drinks.

411
00:20:13,012 --> 00:20:14,647
- Shall we get a move on?
- Let's get to it.

412
00:20:14,647 --> 00:20:17,182
[Everyone To Their Stations]

413
00:20:17,182 --> 00:20:19,785
- Let's make the coffee.
- Yes.

414
00:20:19,785 --> 00:20:21,720
Let's see.

415
00:20:22,688 --> 00:20:24,256
When they bake stuff like madeleines,

416
00:20:24,256 --> 00:20:26,258
we showcase them here.

417
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:32,719
[The Bakery's Main Center Display]

418
00:20:35,034 --> 00:20:39,074
[It Will Soon Be Filled With Desserts]
[Made With Special Local Products]

419
00:20:43,342 --> 00:20:45,024
Look at this, Hee Ae.

420
00:20:45,024 --> 00:20:49,194
This is part of the packaging
for purchased items.

421
00:20:52,117 --> 00:20:55,654
[A Canvas Bag For Takeaway Orders]

422
00:20:56,689 --> 00:20:59,291
How do we use the cash register?

423
00:20:59,291 --> 00:21:00,492
- Do you know how?
- Yes.

424
00:21:00,492 --> 00:21:02,161
If you look here...

425
00:21:02,161 --> 00:21:04,963
Check the numbers, press this button,

426
00:21:04,963 --> 00:21:07,499
and it shows you the total
amount to be paid.

427
00:21:07,499 --> 00:21:08,634
I think that's right.

428
00:21:08,634 --> 00:21:10,794
[An Experienced Pro]

429
00:21:11,437 --> 00:21:14,039
You know your stuff.
You seem experienced.

430
00:21:14,039 --> 00:21:15,541
I did many part-time jobs.

431
00:21:15,541 --> 00:21:16,909
Not in cafés, though.

432
00:21:16,909 --> 00:21:19,712
I worked at beer bars
when I was a university student.

433
00:21:19,712 --> 00:21:21,980
I know the basics,
but technology has advanced.

434
00:21:21,980 --> 00:21:23,782
I heard it's changed a bit.

435
00:21:23,782 --> 00:21:26,485
[Hee Ae Is Relieved]

436
00:21:26,485 --> 00:21:28,226
I don't know where to start.

437
00:21:28,226 --> 00:21:31,295
My head is spinning. I'm so worried.

438
00:21:33,058 --> 00:21:36,951
[Feeling Tense]

439
00:21:45,003 --> 00:21:47,139
Let's start at the beginning.

440
00:21:49,074 --> 00:21:53,243
[Chef Team]
[Green Barley Field Tart Ingredients Check]

441
00:22:03,355 --> 00:22:06,458
- Was it 240 grams?
- Yes, that's right.

442
00:22:06,458 --> 00:22:07,792
Watch the scale.

443
00:22:09,461 --> 00:22:11,362
[Not Quite Enough]

444
00:22:18,090 --> 00:22:19,104
There we go.

445
00:22:19,104 --> 00:22:21,039
- Okay, that's ten.
- All right.

446
00:22:21,673 --> 00:22:23,175
Four hundred.

447
00:22:24,076 --> 00:22:26,211
[Bonjour Green Barley Field Tart]
[400g Flour To Mix With Butter]

448
00:22:26,211 --> 00:22:29,752
[6.8g Green Barley Flour]

449
00:22:33,852 --> 00:22:35,854
- How many grams of salt?
- We need four grams.

450
00:22:35,854 --> 00:22:37,422
We need four grams.

451
00:22:38,423 --> 00:22:40,025
Reset it to zero.

452
00:22:41,193 --> 00:22:42,828
[Bonjour Green Barley Field Tart]
[Add 4g Salt]

453
00:22:42,828 --> 00:22:44,630
There we go.

454
00:22:44,630 --> 00:22:46,698
Ki Taek, can you put this in the fridge?

455
00:22:46,698 --> 00:22:48,700
Sure thing.

456
00:22:50,369 --> 00:22:54,345
[Hall Team]
[Coffee Machine Test]

457
00:22:54,345 --> 00:22:56,275
That's the first step done.

458
00:22:56,275 --> 00:22:57,609
The next step is...

459
00:22:58,944 --> 00:23:00,646
[Testing It The Way He Was Taught]

460
00:23:00,646 --> 00:23:03,315
Put it like this...

461
00:23:09,354 --> 00:23:10,689
And then...

462
00:23:11,957 --> 00:23:14,726
We need to place the cup under the flow.

463
00:23:14,726 --> 00:23:16,294
The next step is...

464
00:23:16,862 --> 00:23:19,097
Let's steam the milk while we wait.

465
00:23:19,665 --> 00:23:20,799
You're good at this.

466
00:23:20,799 --> 00:23:24,102
[You're Doing Great]

467
00:23:24,102 --> 00:23:25,503
And now...

468
00:23:28,941 --> 00:23:30,842
All right, then.

469
00:23:36,882 --> 00:23:39,117
You really remember everything we learned.

470
00:23:39,117 --> 00:23:40,219
I'm trying my best,

471
00:23:40,219 --> 00:23:43,188
- but I'm still not very good.
- That's okay.

472
00:23:43,989 --> 00:23:47,526
[Barista Training Before The Bakery Opening]

473
00:23:47,526 --> 00:23:50,229
- You'll feel it lock in level.
- Okay.

474
00:23:50,229 --> 00:23:51,396
That's it.

475
00:23:51,396 --> 00:23:53,932
Rotate it to the six o'clock position.

476
00:23:53,932 --> 00:23:55,634
And then...

477
00:24:01,106 --> 00:24:03,008
- I need to swirl it in circles.
- That's right.

478
00:24:03,008 --> 00:24:04,776
- Go a little higher.
- Hold on.

479
00:24:04,776 --> 00:24:06,411
Be careful not to go too high.

480
00:24:06,411 --> 00:24:07,880
Keep swirling it...

481
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:10,282
Pour it, and you'll start to see foam.

482
00:24:10,816 --> 00:24:13,385
- I see foam.
- Now tilt the mug up and keep pouring.

483
00:24:13,385 --> 00:24:16,087
- Do you see that foam?
- Yes.

484
00:24:17,789 --> 00:24:19,791
What do you think of my design?

485
00:24:19,791 --> 00:24:20,859
It looks like a cloud.

486
00:24:20,859 --> 00:24:22,828
That's a tough skill,
and you already got one down.

487
00:24:22,828 --> 00:24:24,896
I have, right?

488
00:24:26,131 --> 00:24:28,033
You really remember everything we learned.

489
00:24:28,033 --> 00:24:29,568
[Is It Another Cloud Latte?]
I'm trying my best,

490
00:24:29,568 --> 00:24:32,304
- but I'm still not very good.
- That's okay.

491
00:24:32,804 --> 00:24:34,472
It's looking good.

492
00:24:37,075 --> 00:24:38,410
It's looking good.

493
00:24:38,410 --> 00:24:40,679
[It's A Heart]

494
00:24:40,679 --> 00:24:41,847
I kind of got the hang of it.

495
00:24:41,847 --> 00:24:43,248
Well done.

496
00:24:44,416 --> 00:24:45,550
I've improved, right?

497
00:24:45,550 --> 00:24:47,052
It looks elegant.

498
00:24:55,594 --> 00:24:57,329
- It's so good.
- Does it taste different?

499
00:24:57,329 --> 00:24:59,898
I guess I won't be sleeping tonight.

500
00:25:02,334 --> 00:25:04,238
It's good, right?

501
00:25:04,238 --> 00:25:09,509
[The Bonjour Family Is Nearly Finished
Preparing For Tomorrow]

502
00:25:12,177 --> 00:25:13,278
It was like Crayon Shin-chan.

503
00:25:13,278 --> 00:25:15,414
[The Group Finally Gathers In The Hall
After The Sun Has Set]

504
00:25:15,414 --> 00:25:16,381
Just this section here.
- A sharp cut?
- Yes.

505
00:25:17,349 --> 00:25:20,419
I think they used a clipper.

506
00:25:20,419 --> 00:25:26,791
[Bonjour Bakery]

507
00:25:27,292 --> 00:25:29,027
- Hi.
- Hello.

508
00:25:29,027 --> 00:25:30,495
[The Noodle Delivery Is Here]
Just place them here.

509
00:25:30,495 --> 00:25:32,564
- I'll carry them in.
- Yes, take it inside.

510
00:25:32,564 --> 00:25:34,232
Thank you for the food.

511
00:25:34,232 --> 00:25:35,734
It smells so good.

512
00:25:39,504 --> 00:25:41,339
What's this? Sweet and sour pork?

513
00:25:43,008 --> 00:25:46,444
- Local food is the best.
- Absolutely.

514
00:25:46,812 --> 00:25:48,981
They gave us so much pork.

515
00:25:48,981 --> 00:25:50,949
Same for the spicy seafood noodles.

516
00:25:50,949 --> 00:25:53,752
- It looks so tasty.
- These portions are huge.

517
00:25:56,822 --> 00:25:58,490
It looks delicious.

518
00:25:58,490 --> 00:25:59,958
Take a seat, Hee Ae.

519
00:26:02,294 --> 00:26:04,196
- Let's toast.
- This is so exciting.

520
00:26:04,196 --> 00:26:05,664
- Cheers!
- Good work, team!

521
00:26:05,664 --> 00:26:07,065
Good work.

522
00:26:14,072 --> 00:26:15,540
All right.

523
00:26:17,109 --> 00:26:18,777
That's so tasty.

524
00:26:19,411 --> 00:26:20,579
Eat up, Ki Taek.

525
00:26:20,579 --> 00:26:23,047
- Thank you. Bon appetit.
- Eat up.

526
00:26:31,490 --> 00:26:33,125
It's delicious.

527
00:26:33,125 --> 00:26:34,692
No words needed.

528
00:26:36,962 --> 00:26:41,966
[Too Busy Eating To Talk]

529
00:26:42,367 --> 00:26:45,037
I'm worried about tomorrow.

530
00:26:45,037 --> 00:26:47,439
Since Seon Ho won't be here,

531
00:26:47,439 --> 00:26:49,574
I'm so worried.

532
00:26:51,643 --> 00:26:54,546
Did I just hear that you won't be here?

533
00:26:54,546 --> 00:26:56,081
That's right. We're screwed.

534
00:26:56,081 --> 00:26:57,516
- I have to perform.
- He has a performance.

535
00:26:57,516 --> 00:26:58,483
Tomorrow?

536
00:26:58,483 --> 00:27:00,018
- Yes.
- I have to go.

537
00:27:00,018 --> 00:27:01,853
Will you come back tomorrow?

538
00:27:01,853 --> 00:27:03,555
Yes, I'll come back.

539
00:27:03,555 --> 00:27:04,890
- At that hour?
- Will you be okay?

540
00:27:04,890 --> 00:27:06,725
- You'll get back so late.
- Isn't it too much trouble

541
00:27:06,725 --> 00:27:07,859
- to come all the way back?
- No.

542
00:27:07,859 --> 00:27:10,028
- It's not a problem for me.
- Yes?

543
00:27:11,063 --> 00:27:12,397
It's just a shame

544
00:27:12,397 --> 00:27:15,067
that we prepared together,
but I won't be there for the opening.

545
00:27:15,067 --> 00:27:19,137
There's something meaningful
about going through everything as a team.

546
00:27:19,137 --> 00:27:21,306
The fact that I won't be here...

547
00:27:22,541 --> 00:27:24,042
It makes me a bit sad.

548
00:27:24,042 --> 00:27:25,644
I did try to change my schedule...

549
00:27:25,644 --> 00:27:27,379
- You can't do that.
- Yes.

550
00:27:27,379 --> 00:27:29,614
- It affects other people.
- That's true.

551
00:27:29,614 --> 00:27:32,684
They opened extra tickets because of me.

552
00:27:33,652 --> 00:27:37,956
Fans line the streets to see him,
both morning and night.

553
00:27:37,956 --> 00:27:39,524
He has a huge fanbase.

554
00:27:39,524 --> 00:27:41,059
He's very popular.

555
00:27:41,059 --> 00:27:43,461
[Blushing]

556
00:27:44,296 --> 00:27:47,299
Seon Ho keeps looking at me.

557
00:27:47,299 --> 00:27:48,934
"Would this lady know?"

558
00:27:48,934 --> 00:27:51,570
Oh, come on. That's not it.

559
00:27:51,570 --> 00:27:56,208
Hee Ae is very poised and elegant,
and she doesn't laugh easily.

560
00:27:56,208 --> 00:27:57,742
But when she does laugh,

561
00:27:57,742 --> 00:28:01,313
it's so hearty and infectious

562
00:28:01,313 --> 00:28:05,217
that I keep checking if she's laughing.

563
00:28:05,217 --> 00:28:06,952
I can't help it.

564
00:28:06,952 --> 00:28:08,620
I've played a lot of elegant characters,

565
00:28:08,620 --> 00:28:11,256
but I'm not like that at all in real life.

566
00:28:11,256 --> 00:28:12,924
- What do you mean?
- I just got lucky

567
00:28:12,924 --> 00:28:15,627
with the roles I've gotten to play.

568
00:28:15,627 --> 00:28:18,396
Those expectations put pressure on me.

569
00:28:19,798 --> 00:28:22,300
When you're serving in the hall tomorrow,

570
00:28:22,300 --> 00:28:23,235
will you have a helper?

571
00:28:23,235 --> 00:28:25,403
Why bring up tomorrow at a time like this?

572
00:28:25,403 --> 00:28:27,472
We're talking about life.

573
00:28:27,472 --> 00:28:29,808
Why suddenly bring up work?

574
00:28:29,808 --> 00:28:32,043
Forget it. I'm out.

575
00:28:32,043 --> 00:28:33,845
We were having such a nice conversation.

576
00:28:33,845 --> 00:28:35,046
I shouldn't have said that.

577
00:28:35,046 --> 00:28:37,916
- What if no one comes?
- What?

578
00:28:37,916 --> 00:28:40,084
- It's the opening day, after all.
- Yes, but...

579
00:28:40,485 --> 00:28:43,188
We never know.

580
00:28:43,188 --> 00:28:49,027
Even if we only fill two or three tables,
that will be enough.

581
00:28:49,027 --> 00:28:50,295
[Even Seung Won Is Filled With Worry]

582
00:28:50,295 --> 00:28:52,531
We'll get some customers, right?

583
00:28:52,531 --> 00:28:55,901
[Bonjour Bakery]

584
00:28:55,901 --> 00:29:00,138
[Opening Day]

585
00:29:10,048 --> 00:29:13,818
[From Early In The Morning]

586
00:29:15,654 --> 00:29:19,491
[Every Day Begins In The Field]

587
00:29:19,491 --> 00:29:23,261
[Gapyeong-Ri Hall]
[Gapyeong-Ri Senior Center]

588
00:29:23,261 --> 00:29:26,264
[In The Village Hall]

589
00:29:26,264 --> 00:29:30,635
[Every Day Feels Like The Same Day]

590
00:29:33,538 --> 00:29:38,876
[Can Bonjour Bakery The Small Gift
To Brighten Up Their Daily Lives?]

591
00:29:41,012 --> 00:29:44,482
[Bonjour Bakery]

592
00:30:11,876 --> 00:30:14,445
Let's first turn on the lights.

593
00:30:20,986 --> 00:30:26,331
[Bonjour Bakery Is Open From Today!]

594
00:30:35,500 --> 00:30:37,001
I hope

595
00:30:37,736 --> 00:30:39,904
this table gets used today.

596
00:30:52,684 --> 00:30:55,019
This table is shaky.

597
00:31:36,895 --> 00:31:40,932
[Still Getting Used To This New Work Route]

598
00:31:42,434 --> 00:31:44,702
Hello. Oh, it's you.

599
00:31:45,070 --> 00:31:46,705
Why did you come so early?

600
00:31:46,705 --> 00:31:49,307
I came to get breakfast ready
for you and Hee Ae.

601
00:31:49,307 --> 00:31:50,842
No, don't trouble yourself!

602
00:31:50,842 --> 00:31:52,911
- But you need to eat something.
- I can't believe this.

603
00:31:52,911 --> 00:31:54,446
- I'm also hungry.
- Really?

604
00:31:54,446 --> 00:31:57,849
[The Breakfast He Planned Before Filming]
Yes, so we should eat first.

605
00:31:57,849 --> 00:32:00,418
[At Last, The Morning Prep Begins]

606
00:32:01,419 --> 00:32:04,489
[Chicken Dumplings]

607
00:32:10,628 --> 00:32:12,430
What do you say to two eggs?

608
00:32:12,430 --> 00:32:14,299
- One isn't very filling.
- Sure.

609
00:32:14,299 --> 00:32:15,934
I'll happily eat whatever you whip up.

610
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:18,402
Thank you. I'll do my best.

611
00:32:19,337 --> 00:32:21,840
[Ki Taek's Breakfast Menu 1]

612
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:24,776
[Soft-Boiled Eggs]

613
00:32:24,776 --> 00:32:30,415
[Place Eggs In Boiling Water
For Precisely 10 Minutes]

614
00:32:30,415 --> 00:32:32,083
[Ki Taek's Breakfast Menu 2]

615
00:32:32,083 --> 00:32:35,553
[Berry-Bean-Tomato Detox Juice]

616
00:32:41,025 --> 00:32:44,696
[Mix Blueberry, Black Bean, And Tomato]

617
00:32:44,696 --> 00:32:48,399
[According To Ki Taek's Desired Amount]

618
00:32:49,567 --> 00:32:54,071
[Add Water And Blend It All Together]

619
00:32:55,707 --> 00:33:00,244
[At Last Ki Taek's Long-Awaited Detox Juice]

620
00:33:22,767 --> 00:33:23,935
There is a senior.

621
00:33:23,935 --> 00:33:26,604
Ki Taek, a local is passing by.

622
00:33:32,911 --> 00:33:36,047
It's my first time seeing a local.

623
00:33:37,882 --> 00:33:39,450
Hello, sir.

624
00:33:42,687 --> 00:33:45,490
- We just opened this café today.
- Okay.

625
00:33:45,490 --> 00:33:48,059
You should drop by later
if you get the chance.

626
00:33:48,059 --> 00:33:49,127
Okay.

627
00:33:49,127 --> 00:33:51,062
Have a nice day.

628
00:33:55,133 --> 00:33:57,735
It's my first time meeting a local.

629
00:33:58,937 --> 00:34:02,073
I'd better greet
all the locals who walk past.

630
00:34:02,073 --> 00:34:04,275
I told him to come and visit our new café,

631
00:34:04,275 --> 00:34:05,944
and he just said, "Okay."

632
00:34:05,944 --> 00:34:09,180
He didn't seem very interested.

633
00:34:10,682 --> 00:34:12,283
Hello.

634
00:34:14,185 --> 00:34:17,055
Come and visit our café. We just opened.

635
00:34:17,055 --> 00:34:19,824
Are you Seon Ho?

636
00:34:20,658 --> 00:34:21,726
We just opened.

637
00:34:21,726 --> 00:34:24,462
Drop by if you get the chance.

638
00:34:24,462 --> 00:34:26,097
Can I just drop by whenever?

639
00:34:26,097 --> 00:34:28,099
Yes, but you need to pay.

640
00:34:28,099 --> 00:34:30,268
Is that right?

641
00:34:30,268 --> 00:34:31,336
Of course, I'll pay.

642
00:34:31,336 --> 00:34:33,004
- You live nearby, right?
- Yes.

643
00:34:33,004 --> 00:34:34,239
- Okay.
- Right here.

644
00:34:34,239 --> 00:34:35,640
- That's your house?
- Yes.

645
00:34:35,640 --> 00:34:38,243
You should definitely come by
since you live so close.

646
00:34:38,243 --> 00:34:39,844
- Have a nice day.
- You too.

647
00:34:39,844 --> 00:34:41,312
Thank you.

648
00:34:47,218 --> 00:34:50,121
- Bonjour!
- Hello.

649
00:34:51,723 --> 00:34:53,191
Bonjour.

650
00:34:53,191 --> 00:34:55,026
Bonjour, Seung Won.

651
00:34:55,026 --> 00:34:59,497
[Straight After Arriving,
They Put On Their Chef Uniform]

652
00:35:02,567 --> 00:35:06,537
[They Even Put On Kitchen Shoes]

653
00:35:09,407 --> 00:35:11,876
Hello, ma'am.

654
00:35:11,876 --> 00:35:14,445
[Lastly, The Manager Has Arrived]
Come and visit our café.

655
00:35:14,445 --> 00:35:16,014
We open today.

656
00:35:16,014 --> 00:35:18,149
- You're open?
- Yes.

657
00:35:18,950 --> 00:35:20,218
- We open at 11 a.m.
- Okay.

658
00:35:20,218 --> 00:35:24,221
[Bonjour Bakery Hours]
11 a.m. TO 6 p.m.

659
00:35:26,090 --> 00:35:28,326
- Good morning.
- Good morning, Hee Ae.

660
00:35:28,326 --> 00:35:31,128
- You're early, like a model student.
- Yes.

661
00:35:32,096 --> 00:35:33,999
- Did you sleep well?
- Did you?

662
00:35:33,999 --> 00:35:34,999
I did.

663
00:35:34,999 --> 00:35:36,534
Of course, I didn't.

664
00:35:36,534 --> 00:35:37,802
[Manager Hee Ae Was Too Nervous To Sleep]

665
00:35:37,802 --> 00:35:39,237
Do you want a cup of coffee?

666
00:35:39,237 --> 00:35:41,372
- Yes, please.
- Hot or cold?

667
00:35:41,372 --> 00:35:43,107
- I like my coffee hot.
- Hot it is.

668
00:35:43,107 --> 00:35:45,877
- Make it decaf, please.
- Coming right up.

669
00:35:45,877 --> 00:35:48,780
[Another Staff Member Is Joining Today]

670
00:35:48,780 --> 00:35:51,082
I won't be here tomorrow,
so just try it out for one day.

671
00:35:51,082 --> 00:35:52,483
We don't have Seon Ho.

672
00:35:52,483 --> 00:35:55,086
[Seon Ho Can't Stay For The Opening]

673
00:35:55,086 --> 00:35:57,589
Do you know who's coming?

674
00:35:57,589 --> 00:36:00,024
He's the youngest member of Seventeen.

675
00:36:00,024 --> 00:36:02,894
[Youngest Of Seventeen?]
His name is Dino.

676
00:36:02,894 --> 00:36:04,228
They have a big fanbase in Korea,

677
00:36:04,228 --> 00:36:05,697
- but especially abroad
- Global fans.

678
00:36:05,697 --> 00:36:06,898
In places like Japan.

679
00:36:06,898 --> 00:36:08,166
- Seventeen?
- Yes.

680
00:36:08,166 --> 00:36:09,367
Like you can't imagine.

681
00:36:09,367 --> 00:36:10,404
[A Globally Famous Part-Timer]

682
00:36:10,404 --> 00:36:13,899
[That Impressive Part-Timer Is On His Way]

683
00:36:16,774 --> 00:36:19,420
[He Looks Nervous Even From Behind]

684
00:36:21,012 --> 00:36:24,315
[Anxious And Short Of Breath]

685
00:36:24,315 --> 00:36:27,852
[He Speedwalks To Bonjour Bakery]

686
00:36:27,852 --> 00:36:29,988
[Seventeen's Dino]

687
00:36:29,988 --> 00:36:32,757
[Seventeen's Main Dancer]

688
00:36:32,757 --> 00:36:35,760
[And The Youngest Of The 13 Members]

689
00:36:35,760 --> 00:36:38,396
[Here Comes The Pro Youngest To The Rescue]

690
00:36:41,532 --> 00:36:42,933
Hello.

691
00:36:43,901 --> 00:36:46,838
- Hello.
- Hello.

692
00:36:46,838 --> 00:36:48,606
- Thanks for coming all this way.
- Not at all.

693
00:36:48,606 --> 00:36:49,807
- It's nice to meet you.
- Seventeen.

694
00:36:49,807 --> 00:36:52,246
- Dino.
- Nice to meet you.

695
00:36:52,246 --> 00:36:54,045
[The Kitchen Team Also Greets Him Warmly]
Welcome.

696
00:36:54,045 --> 00:36:55,513
- Your hands are so cold.
- Hello.

697
00:36:55,513 --> 00:36:56,614
It's nice to meet you.

698
00:36:56,614 --> 00:36:59,116
- It's a pleasure to meet you.
- Same here.

699
00:37:00,485 --> 00:37:01,586
Thank you for helping out.

700
00:37:01,586 --> 00:37:03,654
Not at all. It's my pleasure.

701
00:37:04,042 --> 00:37:06,157
I have to go and perform,

702
00:37:06,157 --> 00:37:08,459
- so you need to stay for a day.
- That's right.

703
00:37:08,459 --> 00:37:09,727
How early did you have to set out?

704
00:37:09,727 --> 00:37:11,496
- Me?
- Yes.

705
00:37:11,496 --> 00:37:13,197
I didn't get here this morning.

706
00:37:13,197 --> 00:37:17,035
- I came yesterday after filming wrapped.
- Oh, that's good.

707
00:37:17,035 --> 00:37:18,569
- Good job.
- Yes.

708
00:37:18,569 --> 00:37:20,271
- You stayed nearby.
- I feel so nervous.

709
00:37:20,271 --> 00:37:21,773
Are you nervous?

710
00:37:21,773 --> 00:37:23,741
I've never done a part-time job before.

711
00:37:23,741 --> 00:37:25,576
- It's your first part-time experience?
- Yes.

712
00:37:25,576 --> 00:37:26,978
Let's work hard together.

713
00:37:26,978 --> 00:37:28,246
Okay.

714
00:37:28,246 --> 00:37:29,647
By the way,

715
00:37:29,647 --> 00:37:32,283
- you know Manager Hee Ae.
- Yes?

716
00:37:32,283 --> 00:37:33,551
- She will help.
- Absolutely.

717
00:37:33,551 --> 00:37:35,653
- You can trust her to show you the ropes.
- Absolutely.

718
00:37:35,653 --> 00:37:36,888
If nothing else...

719
00:37:36,888 --> 00:37:38,089
Thank you.

720
00:37:38,089 --> 00:37:41,926
She has more experience
than you can imagine.

721
00:37:41,926 --> 00:37:42,927
You can trust her.

722
00:37:42,927 --> 00:37:45,163
You'll see why she's a legend.

723
00:37:45,163 --> 00:37:46,064
[Just Trust Manager Hee Ae]

724
00:37:46,064 --> 00:37:47,365
You'll know after just one hour with her.

725
00:37:47,365 --> 00:37:49,400
- Seriously.
- I place myself in your hands.

726
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:52,270
- You'll feel like you can just relax.
- Okay.

727
00:37:52,270 --> 00:37:54,072
I'm telling you.

728
00:37:54,072 --> 00:37:55,306
Oh, come on.

729
00:37:59,477 --> 00:38:02,080
Oh, these are descriptions.

730
00:38:02,080 --> 00:38:04,348
- We'll hand them out with the menus.
- Right.

731
00:38:05,016 --> 00:38:07,685
The senior customers
can learn about the dessert,

732
00:38:08,553 --> 00:38:10,554
and it adds to the fun.

733
00:38:11,856 --> 00:38:12,957
[Dessert Cards To Go With The Desserts]

734
00:38:12,957 --> 00:38:14,459
This is a description card.

735
00:38:14,459 --> 00:38:16,094
If you read it while you eat,

736
00:38:16,094 --> 00:38:17,995
it can make the dessert more enjoyable.

737
00:38:19,597 --> 00:38:21,499
I got it.

738
00:38:24,102 --> 00:38:26,204
For breakfast today,

739
00:38:26,204 --> 00:38:28,272
we planned to have
things like boiled eggs.

740
00:38:28,272 --> 00:38:30,641
Are you okay with that?

741
00:38:30,641 --> 00:38:32,110
- Along with the boiled eggs,
- Okay.

742
00:38:32,110 --> 00:38:35,113
I blended blueberries,
black beans, and tomatoes

743
00:38:35,113 --> 00:38:37,415
- for a morning smoothie.
- Sounds great.

744
00:38:37,415 --> 00:38:38,483
What would Ki Taek have done

745
00:38:38,483 --> 00:38:41,285
if there weren't any
blueberries or tomatoes?

746
00:38:41,285 --> 00:38:42,653
- Are you okay with it?
- It sounds great.

747
00:38:42,653 --> 00:38:46,224
What would he have done
without tomatoes and blueberries?

748
00:38:46,224 --> 00:38:49,227
If there were no eggs,
blueberries, and tomatoes...

749
00:38:49,227 --> 00:38:52,830
[He's Obsessed With Making]
[The Staff Breakfast]

750
00:38:53,231 --> 00:38:55,233
Do you like iced Americano, Dino?

751
00:38:55,233 --> 00:38:56,134
Oh, well...

752
00:38:56,134 --> 00:38:58,002
Or would you prefer something like tea?

753
00:38:58,002 --> 00:38:59,937
- I'll have some coffee.
- You want coffee?

754
00:38:59,937 --> 00:39:01,539
- Hot or cold?
- Hot, please.

755
00:39:01,539 --> 00:39:03,207
- Hot?
- Yes, thank you.

756
00:39:03,207 --> 00:39:05,143
Perhaps I should learn to make it now.

757
00:39:05,143 --> 00:39:07,611
- Would you like to?
- I can learn by watching

758
00:39:08,012 --> 00:39:10,014
- over your shoulder.
- But the thing is...

759
00:39:10,014 --> 00:39:11,516
- There's not much to it.
- Okay.

760
00:39:11,516 --> 00:39:13,885
[Barista Seon Ho Passes The Baton]
The machines are all ready to go.

761
00:39:13,885 --> 00:39:16,220
When you take this out,
this part is always empty.

762
00:39:16,220 --> 00:39:17,822
- Okay.
- But since this part here

763
00:39:17,822 --> 00:39:19,157
comes into contact with the coffee,

764
00:39:19,157 --> 00:39:21,238
always do this before you pull the shot.

765
00:39:21,238 --> 00:39:22,226
[Cleanliness Is Key]

766
00:39:22,226 --> 00:39:23,761
- You need to give it a quick wipe.
- Okay.

767
00:39:23,761 --> 00:39:24,996
Then place it here.

768
00:39:24,996 --> 00:39:26,767
[Dose The Coffee First]

769
00:39:26,767 --> 00:39:31,369
[Dosing: Placing A Measured Amount Of Ground Coffee
Into The Filter Basket For Extraction]

770
00:39:31,369 --> 00:39:33,938
- Once that's been extracted,
- Yes.

771
00:39:33,938 --> 00:39:35,773
- You see this mound?
- Yes.

772
00:39:35,773 --> 00:39:38,109
Bring it over here,

773
00:39:38,109 --> 00:39:40,912
[Level The Mound Of Coffee]
and gently tap it like this.

774
00:39:40,912 --> 00:39:44,282
The grounds move in the direction you tap.

775
00:39:44,282 --> 00:39:46,584
- This is called tamping.
- "Tamping."

776
00:39:46,584 --> 00:39:48,886
While it's in this position,

777
00:39:48,886 --> 00:39:53,224
check the level
with your thumb and index finger.

778
00:39:53,224 --> 00:39:55,927
- When it's somewhat level,
- Yes?

779
00:39:55,927 --> 00:39:59,263
- It looks like this.
- Okay.

780
00:39:59,263 --> 00:40:01,199
- If it doesn't fall out,
- Yes.

781
00:40:01,199 --> 00:40:03,100
[Perfect Tamping]
that means it's ready.

782
00:40:03,100 --> 00:40:04,368
[Feeling Pleased With Himself]

783
00:40:04,368 --> 00:40:05,469
One more thing

784
00:40:05,469 --> 00:40:08,372
you must always do
before the extraction...

785
00:40:08,372 --> 00:40:10,141
- Thank you.
- Why all of a sudden?

786
00:40:10,141 --> 00:40:12,643
[Supportive Manager Hee Ae]
Press this button first.

787
00:40:12,643 --> 00:40:14,579
Why don't you start with this?

788
00:40:14,579 --> 00:40:16,147
So, I do this...

789
00:40:16,147 --> 00:40:18,850
In the eight o'clock position.

790
00:40:18,850 --> 00:40:20,651
That's it. It locks, right?

791
00:40:20,651 --> 00:40:22,787
- Now turn it to the six o'clock position.
- Okay.

792
00:40:22,787 --> 00:40:25,056
That's the standard lock-in position.

793
00:40:25,056 --> 00:40:27,692
That's all there is to extracting coffee.

794
00:40:27,692 --> 00:40:29,927
You just need to move it
from eight o'clock to six o'clock.

795
00:40:29,927 --> 00:40:31,395
- From eight to six.
- You've got it.

796
00:40:31,395 --> 00:40:33,264
- That's how you do it.
- Okay.

797
00:40:33,264 --> 00:40:36,367
[Fully Lock It In Then Pull The Shot]

798
00:40:37,134 --> 00:40:39,570
- Okay.
- Move it back to eight o'clock.

799
00:40:39,570 --> 00:40:40,972
I'm moving it back to eight o'clock.

800
00:40:40,972 --> 00:40:42,106
That's it.

801
00:40:42,106 --> 00:40:43,074
- And then...
- Then,

802
00:40:43,074 --> 00:40:45,142
- since there's residue...
- Oh, right.

803
00:40:45,142 --> 00:40:46,137
[Hands-On Intensive Training]

804
00:40:46,777 --> 00:40:48,512
Wipe it down.

805
00:40:48,980 --> 00:40:50,547
You're a fast learner.

806
00:40:51,382 --> 00:40:52,283
Press firmly.

807
00:40:52,283 --> 00:40:54,619
Not too hard. That's fine.

808
00:40:54,619 --> 00:40:56,454
[A Fast-Learning Part-Timer]
And then you... Perfect.

809
00:40:56,454 --> 00:40:57,988
- Put it in here...
- Yes.

810
00:41:00,358 --> 00:41:02,860
Move it from eight o'clock to...

811
00:41:03,728 --> 00:41:05,729
That's okay. Take it slow.

812
00:41:08,900 --> 00:41:10,134
Eight o'clock.

813
00:41:10,134 --> 00:41:11,736
That's it. You're doing great.

814
00:41:11,736 --> 00:41:13,137
You got it in the right position.

815
00:41:13,137 --> 00:41:15,773
[Successfully Rotated
To The 6 O'clock Position]

816
00:41:15,773 --> 00:41:17,174
You've mastered it.

817
00:41:17,174 --> 00:41:18,809
- You can get started.
- Okay.

818
00:41:18,809 --> 00:41:21,279
You should also practice
making an iced Americano.

819
00:41:21,279 --> 00:41:23,213
- I do.
- All right.

820
00:41:24,015 --> 00:41:25,049
It's easy, right?

821
00:41:25,049 --> 00:41:26,284
Not really.

822
00:41:26,284 --> 00:41:28,052
[It's Harder Than Expected]

823
00:41:28,052 --> 00:41:30,922
Honestly, I just got the hang of it.

824
00:41:30,922 --> 00:41:33,257
It's definitely not easy.

825
00:41:35,092 --> 00:41:37,895
- Can I address you casually?
- Of course.

826
00:41:37,895 --> 00:41:39,697
- I'll also keep it casual.
- Okay.

827
00:41:39,697 --> 00:41:41,732
- Is that okay?
- Yes.

828
00:41:41,732 --> 00:41:44,302
I wish you didn't have to leave today.

829
00:41:44,302 --> 00:41:47,071
- Oh, man. I'm so sorry.
- No, don't be.

830
00:41:47,071 --> 00:41:48,839
I wish I could stay.

831
00:41:48,839 --> 00:41:50,441
I feel like I still have more to learn.

832
00:41:50,441 --> 00:41:53,344
- I can't pull out of this event.
- I know.

833
00:41:53,344 --> 00:41:57,648
[Meanwhile In The Kitchen]

834
00:41:58,082 --> 00:42:01,490
[Seung Won Looks Over The Dessert Recipes]

835
00:42:07,692 --> 00:42:12,897
[Introducing Bonjour Bakery's
Morning Dessert Line-Up]

836
00:42:12,897 --> 00:42:15,032
[From Gochang's Spacious Fields]

837
00:42:15,032 --> 00:42:18,536
[And Large Coastlines]

838
00:42:18,536 --> 00:42:22,606
[Made With Local Ingredients]

839
00:42:22,606 --> 00:42:25,443
[Bonjour Bakery's Special Desserts]

840
00:42:25,443 --> 00:42:28,729
[A Dessert Evoking Gochang's
Sun-Nurtured Green Barley Fields]

841
00:42:29,613 --> 00:42:33,525
[Bonjour Green Barley Field Tart]

842
00:42:33,951 --> 00:42:35,619
[A Dessert Made From Sweet Potato]

843
00:42:35,619 --> 00:42:38,288
[That Was Grown In Fertile Soil]

844
00:42:38,823 --> 00:42:41,726
[Bonjour Sweet Potato Cake]

845
00:42:41,726 --> 00:42:43,828
[The Classic French Dessert]
[Crème Brûlée]

846
00:42:43,828 --> 00:42:46,998
[3 Hours Before Opening]

847
00:42:46,998 --> 00:42:50,267
[Cha Loaf Bread Prep]

848
00:42:53,371 --> 00:42:56,040
[Cha Loaf Bread]
[It's On The Afternoon Menu]

849
00:42:56,040 --> 00:42:58,742
[But The Yeast Needs Time To Rise]

850
00:43:00,878 --> 00:43:04,481
[The Dough Is Made
Of Just Flour, Water, And Milk]

851
00:43:31,375 --> 00:43:33,811
[Dough Ready]

852
00:43:38,416 --> 00:43:42,686
[Proof At Room Temperature For 30 Minutes]

853
00:43:42,686 --> 00:43:44,255
[Prepare The Crème Brûlée Filling]

854
00:43:44,255 --> 00:43:46,257
- Reset it to zero for me.
- Yes, sir.

855
00:43:46,257 --> 00:43:48,759
[Prepare The Crème Brûlée Filling]

856
00:43:48,759 --> 00:43:50,327
I'll start right away.

857
00:43:50,895 --> 00:43:56,233
[Mix The Sugar And Yolk]

858
00:44:05,309 --> 00:44:07,878
[Showing Off His Mixing Skills]

859
00:44:07,878 --> 00:44:09,680
This is how it's done.

860
00:44:09,680 --> 00:44:11,915
You can't be all work and no play.

861
00:44:12,716 --> 00:44:16,353
[After Mixing The Yolk And Sugar Happily]

862
00:44:16,353 --> 00:44:21,258
[Add The Heated Cream With Vanilla Beans]

863
00:44:26,297 --> 00:44:29,266
[Endless Mixing Grind]

864
00:44:31,969 --> 00:44:33,804
I'm in a playful mood.

865
00:44:33,804 --> 00:44:36,040
Why do I feel so energized today?

866
00:44:36,040 --> 00:44:38,775
- It's hard to keep up.
- Maybe I'll crash just as suddenly.

867
00:44:39,143 --> 00:44:41,479
- It's a recipe for injury,
- Really?

868
00:44:41,479 --> 00:44:43,280
Like when I get overexcited
in action scenes.

869
00:44:43,280 --> 00:44:45,015
It's a disaster waiting to happen.

870
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:49,520
[Meanwhile, The Sous Chef Is Feeling Tense]

871
00:44:50,154 --> 00:44:54,691
[Carefully Mix It All With A Hand Blender]

872
00:44:56,227 --> 00:44:58,028
[Is He Doing Well?]

873
00:45:05,636 --> 00:45:07,004
Don't let it foam.

874
00:45:07,004 --> 00:45:09,273
- I made it foam too much.
- That's okay.

875
00:45:11,442 --> 00:45:14,282
[Portion Out The Vanilla Filling]

876
00:45:17,548 --> 00:45:19,848
[After Repeating This Process]

877
00:45:22,753 --> 00:45:23,987
Okay.

878
00:45:24,555 --> 00:45:27,291
I think I just need to fill it halfway.

879
00:45:27,291 --> 00:45:28,484
[Bake In A Water Bath For 30 Minutes]

880
00:45:29,193 --> 00:45:31,094
That's finished.

881
00:45:32,062 --> 00:45:34,632
[After The Baking,
It Must Be Cooled At Room Temperature]

882
00:45:34,632 --> 00:45:36,500
[And Then Cooled In A Fridge]

883
00:45:37,134 --> 00:45:41,438
[The Smell Of Bread Fills The Neighborhood]

884
00:45:45,342 --> 00:45:49,446
[Senior Café]
[Bonjour Bakery]

885
00:45:49,446 --> 00:45:52,883
[It's Enough To Stop A Local In His Tracks]

886
00:45:52,883 --> 00:45:54,785
- Hello.
- Hello.

887
00:45:55,486 --> 00:45:57,421
I came over out of curiosity.

888
00:45:57,421 --> 00:45:59,223
- I see.
- Yes.

889
00:45:59,223 --> 00:46:01,025
What kind of place is this?

890
00:46:01,025 --> 00:46:03,594
It's a dessert café.

891
00:46:03,594 --> 00:46:05,796
- A dessert café?
- Yes.

892
00:46:05,796 --> 00:46:09,032
"You must be over 65 years old to enter."

893
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:11,268
Young people aren't allowed in?

894
00:46:11,268 --> 00:46:13,971
No, young people are also welcome,

895
00:46:13,971 --> 00:46:18,041
but they need to be accompanied
by a senior who is 65 or older.

896
00:46:18,676 --> 00:46:19,710
Is that right?

897
00:46:19,710 --> 00:46:21,645
You're welcome to take a look around.

898
00:46:21,645 --> 00:46:23,547
- Can we?
- Yes, come on in.

899
00:46:23,547 --> 00:46:26,217
I wondered what the remodeling was for.

900
00:46:26,217 --> 00:46:28,219
- Hello.
- They're just here to look around.

901
00:46:28,219 --> 00:46:29,954
- Hello.
- Hello.

902
00:46:29,954 --> 00:46:32,323
[The Unexpected First Guests Of The Day]

903
00:46:32,323 --> 00:46:34,725
Look at all the cooking equipment.

904
00:46:34,725 --> 00:46:36,060
Please come again for a proper visit.

905
00:46:36,060 --> 00:46:37,595
We've got everything set up nicely.

906
00:46:37,595 --> 00:46:39,330
Of course.

907
00:46:39,330 --> 00:46:41,999
Right now, inside the kitchen...

908
00:46:41,999 --> 00:46:44,201
- Do you know Cha Seung Won?
- Yes.

909
00:46:44,201 --> 00:46:47,204
- He's making the desserts right now.
- That's right.

910
00:46:47,204 --> 00:46:49,039
He's making them as we speak.

911
00:46:49,039 --> 00:46:52,209
[Enthusiastically Whisking Away]

912
00:46:52,209 --> 00:46:54,700
- I told you they were famous.
- Are they?

913
00:46:54,700 --> 00:46:55,679
That's right.

914
00:46:55,679 --> 00:46:58,349
- They're famous.
- Thanks for letting us browse.

915
00:46:58,349 --> 00:46:59,250
Of course.

916
00:46:59,250 --> 00:47:01,185
- But you have to come back.
- We'll drop by regularly.

917
00:47:01,185 --> 00:47:02,119
- Thank you.
- Bye.

918
00:47:02,119 --> 00:47:03,854
Goodbye.

919
00:47:04,922 --> 00:47:06,890
Who are they?

920
00:47:06,890 --> 00:47:08,559
- What?
- Them.

921
00:47:08,559 --> 00:47:09,860
Who was that?

922
00:47:09,860 --> 00:47:11,362
- That was Kim Hee Ae.
- What?

923
00:47:11,362 --> 00:47:13,564
- She's a famous actress.
- Oh, right.

924
00:47:13,564 --> 00:47:15,365
Have you never heard of her?

925
00:47:16,634 --> 00:47:17,801
Hello.

926
00:47:17,801 --> 00:47:19,069
[Hee Ae Is Out To Attract Guests]

927
00:47:19,069 --> 00:47:20,804
We're officially open from today.

928
00:47:20,804 --> 00:47:22,806
Did you know that?

929
00:47:23,207 --> 00:47:25,275
Come by later.

930
00:47:35,152 --> 00:47:36,887
Hello.

931
00:47:39,123 --> 00:47:42,159
Do you know we just
opened a new dessert café?

932
00:47:42,159 --> 00:47:43,794
We had no idea.

933
00:47:43,794 --> 00:47:48,331
We sell delicious desserts.

934
00:47:49,700 --> 00:47:53,203
Aren't you a famous celebrity?

935
00:47:53,203 --> 00:47:54,705
- Yes, I am.
- Right?

936
00:47:54,705 --> 00:47:55,939
That's right.

937
00:47:55,939 --> 00:47:57,841
- Do you know who I am?
- It's nice to meet you.

938
00:47:57,841 --> 00:47:59,843
- The pleasure is mine.
- You're Kim...

939
00:47:59,843 --> 00:48:01,211
[Of Course I Know Who You Are]

940
00:48:01,211 --> 00:48:03,414
What was it?

941
00:48:03,414 --> 00:48:05,215
- My name?
- Yes.

942
00:48:05,215 --> 00:48:06,383
- Kim...
- Yes, Kim.

943
00:48:06,383 --> 00:48:07,818
Mi-ae.

944
00:48:07,818 --> 00:48:09,319
It's close.

945
00:48:09,887 --> 00:48:11,622
- It's Kim Hee Ae.
- That's right.

946
00:48:11,622 --> 00:48:13,090
[My Name Is Kim Hee Ae]

947
00:48:13,090 --> 00:48:15,092
- It's nice to meet you.
- Nice meeting you.

948
00:48:15,092 --> 00:48:16,694
Drop by later.

949
00:48:16,694 --> 00:48:17,928
We open at 11 a.m.

950
00:48:17,928 --> 00:48:20,864
What's a famous lady like you
doing in the countryside?

951
00:48:20,864 --> 00:48:22,199
It's so lovely here.

952
00:48:22,199 --> 00:48:24,335
Take a stroll around if you have the time.
It's nice here.

953
00:48:24,335 --> 00:48:28,072
Yes, it's so quiet and charming.

954
00:48:28,072 --> 00:48:29,973
- I'll see you later.
- All right.

955
00:48:29,973 --> 00:48:33,644
[Please Come And Visit]

956
00:48:33,644 --> 00:48:36,013
[Time For A Solid Breakfast
After All That Hard Work]

957
00:48:36,013 --> 00:48:38,381
[Ki Taek's Boiled Eggs]

958
00:48:40,050 --> 00:48:44,188
[Manager Hee Ae Approves]

959
00:48:44,188 --> 00:48:45,689
- Ki Taek.
- Yes?

960
00:48:45,689 --> 00:48:47,257
These eggs are so well boiled.

961
00:48:47,257 --> 00:48:49,059
- It's easy to peel, right?
- It peels right off.

962
00:48:49,059 --> 00:48:50,661
Right?

963
00:48:50,661 --> 00:48:51,995
I met some seniors...

964
00:48:51,995 --> 00:48:54,064
[The Hall Team That Was Busy
With The Handover]

965
00:48:54,531 --> 00:48:59,636
[Also Fills Up On Ki Taek's
Healthy Breakfast]

966
00:49:02,439 --> 00:49:05,078
[20 Minutes Before Opening]

967
00:49:08,645 --> 00:49:13,556
[Is It Open?]

968
00:49:13,556 --> 00:49:16,875
[Is It Closed?]

969
00:49:19,990 --> 00:49:22,696
[12 Minutes Before Opening]

970
00:49:25,162 --> 00:49:27,995
[So Curious]

971
00:49:30,434 --> 00:49:31,902
- I'll get going now.
- Go ahead.

972
00:49:31,902 --> 00:49:33,670
Go about your business. I'll take over.

973
00:49:33,670 --> 00:49:34,905
Good luck!

974
00:49:34,905 --> 00:49:36,373
- Good luck.
- We've got this!

975
00:49:36,373 --> 00:49:37,475
[Seon Ho Has To Leave For His Performance]

976
00:49:37,475 --> 00:49:39,843
Can I really go?
Will you be okay?

977
00:49:39,843 --> 00:49:42,313
You know how to make a latte now.

978
00:49:42,313 --> 00:49:45,282
Have a safe trip.
Take your time getting back.

979
00:49:45,282 --> 00:49:47,450
- I'll just say goodbye to Seung Won.
- Sure.

980
00:49:48,218 --> 00:49:49,453
- Hey, Seon Ho.
- Yes?

981
00:49:49,453 --> 00:49:51,088
Good luck.

982
00:49:51,088 --> 00:49:52,623
Thank you.

983
00:49:52,623 --> 00:49:54,191
- By the way,
- Yes?

984
00:49:54,191 --> 00:49:56,527
Don't put yourself out by rushing back.

985
00:49:56,527 --> 00:49:59,329
- We'll be closed by then anyway.
- Okay.

986
00:49:59,329 --> 00:50:00,531
Hurry up and get going.

987
00:50:00,531 --> 00:50:01,698
Yes, go ahead.

988
00:50:01,698 --> 00:50:03,600
- Good luck.
- Bye.

989
00:50:04,201 --> 00:50:05,402
- Good luck!
- You too.

990
00:50:05,402 --> 00:50:06,537
Thanks for showing me the ropes.

991
00:50:06,537 --> 00:50:07,471
- Dino.
- Yes?

992
00:50:07,471 --> 00:50:08,605
Just one more thing. Come here.

993
00:50:08,605 --> 00:50:10,007
- Sorry?
- Come along.

994
00:50:10,007 --> 00:50:12,643
- You need to write today's menu on here.
- Okay.

995
00:50:12,643 --> 00:50:14,778
Write it here like this.

996
00:50:14,778 --> 00:50:15,846
Today's menu...

997
00:50:15,846 --> 00:50:17,414
I wish I had better handwriting.

998
00:50:17,414 --> 00:50:20,283
- If only!
- My writing's terrible, too.

999
00:50:21,218 --> 00:50:23,454
- I'd do it, but I don't have time.
- Sure.

1000
00:50:23,454 --> 00:50:25,655
- I'll see you later.
- Okay

1001
00:50:26,089 --> 00:50:28,192
- Good luck.
- Good luck!

1002
00:50:28,192 --> 00:50:32,267
[10:55 a.m.]

1003
00:50:32,930 --> 00:50:36,333
[Writing Up Today's Dessert Menu]

1004
00:50:42,539 --> 00:50:44,141
Green Barley Field Tart.

1005
00:50:44,141 --> 00:50:46,810
[Introducing]

1006
00:50:46,810 --> 00:50:49,513
[Bonjour Bakery's 1st Morning Menu
Green Barley Field Tart]

1007
00:50:49,513 --> 00:50:51,515
[Bonjour Crème Brûlée]

1008
00:50:51,515 --> 00:50:54,118
[Bonjour Sweet Potato Cake]

1009
00:50:54,118 --> 00:50:57,090
[2 Types Of Baked Goods]
[Bonjour Citron Madeleine]

1010
00:50:57,090 --> 00:50:59,664
[Bonjour Financier]

1011
00:51:03,794 --> 00:51:05,796
How does this look, Hee Ae?

1012
00:51:05,796 --> 00:51:07,664
Should I put in one more?
Or is four better?

1013
00:51:07,664 --> 00:51:10,834
- It looks nicer when there's more of them.
- You think?

1014
00:51:10,834 --> 00:51:13,003
- It looks more impressive.
- Let's just leave it.

1015
00:51:13,003 --> 00:51:14,738
- Okay.
- Five is good.

1016
00:51:28,519 --> 00:51:29,920
Okay.

1017
00:51:38,362 --> 00:51:41,431
[We Are Open]

1018
00:51:49,706 --> 00:51:53,012
[Day One, Open For Business]

1019
00:51:53,944 --> 00:51:56,346
If we do get customers,

1020
00:51:56,346 --> 00:51:58,181
how should we greet them?

1021
00:51:58,181 --> 00:51:59,249
"Welcome"?

1022
00:51:59,249 --> 00:52:00,984
- Hello is fine.
- Just hello?

1023
00:52:00,984 --> 00:52:02,390
- Yes, let's just say hello.
- Okay.

1024
00:52:02,390 --> 00:52:03,420
Hello.

1025
00:52:03,420 --> 00:52:04,421
[Hall Team's Greeting Protocol]

1026
00:52:04,421 --> 00:52:07,124
[Cheerfully Say "Hello"]

1027
00:52:07,124 --> 00:52:08,858
Hello!

1028
00:52:10,360 --> 00:52:12,195
They're coming in.

1029
00:52:12,930 --> 00:52:15,398
[Dino Goes Outside To Look Around]

1030
00:52:16,603 --> 00:52:19,183
[3 Women Are Lingering Close By]

1031
00:52:20,103 --> 00:52:21,538
Are there people inside?

1032
00:52:21,538 --> 00:52:23,006
I don't think anyone's in.

1033
00:52:23,006 --> 00:52:24,359
I think the store is empty.

1034
00:52:24,359 --> 00:52:25,409
I think you're right.

1035
00:52:25,409 --> 00:52:27,811
[Just As They Were About To Walk Past...]

1036
00:52:29,313 --> 00:52:31,381
- Hello!
- Hello.

1037
00:52:32,249 --> 00:52:33,283
Are you coming in?

1038
00:52:33,283 --> 00:52:35,018
- Yes.
- Welcome!

1039
00:52:35,018 --> 00:52:36,453
- Are we welcome?
- Yes.

1040
00:52:36,453 --> 00:52:37,688
We have guests.

1041
00:52:37,688 --> 00:52:40,490
Hello.

1042
00:52:40,490 --> 00:52:41,395
Come on in.

1043
00:52:41,395 --> 00:52:43,006
[These Faces Seem Familiar]

1044
00:52:43,727 --> 00:52:45,295
Aren't you a famous celebrity?

1045
00:52:45,295 --> 00:52:46,863
- Yes, I am.
- Right?

1046
00:52:46,863 --> 00:52:48,365
Drop by later.

1047
00:52:48,365 --> 00:52:50,238
[The Locals Hee Ae Chatted With]
We open at 11 a.m.

1048
00:52:50,767 --> 00:52:51,935
She's that celebrity.

1049
00:52:51,935 --> 00:52:53,036
Oh, my.

1050
00:52:53,036 --> 00:52:55,305
Hello, nice to see you.

1051
00:52:55,305 --> 00:52:57,007
I've seen you on TV.

1052
00:52:57,674 --> 00:52:59,343
To come here,

1053
00:52:59,343 --> 00:53:01,678
- you must be over 65 years old.
- Yes, 65.

1054
00:53:01,678 --> 00:53:03,914
- I need to see your IDs.
- I didn't bring it.

1055
00:53:03,914 --> 00:53:06,383
- Over 65 years old?
- Are you sure you're over 65?

1056
00:53:06,383 --> 00:53:08,352
- Yes, I am.
- All right, then.

1057
00:53:08,352 --> 00:53:10,520
- I was born in the '50s.
- All right.

1058
00:53:10,520 --> 00:53:12,756
- You just look so young.
- Really?

1059
00:53:12,756 --> 00:53:16,393
Why, thank you.

1060
00:53:16,393 --> 00:53:18,328
Thanks for thinking we look young.

1061
00:53:18,328 --> 00:53:20,831
We've come a long way.

1062
00:53:20,831 --> 00:53:22,466
Having a café like this in our town.

1063
00:53:22,466 --> 00:53:25,502
She looks just like my oldest daughter.

1064
00:53:25,502 --> 00:53:26,570
She does!

1065
00:53:26,570 --> 00:53:28,105
- They look alike.
- They do.

1066
00:53:28,105 --> 00:53:30,140
It's nice seeing someone like you here.

1067
00:53:30,140 --> 00:53:31,608
Who looks like whose oldest daughter?

1068
00:53:31,608 --> 00:53:33,276
Thank you.

1069
00:53:33,276 --> 00:53:36,112
Ask if her daughter runs this bakery.

1070
00:53:36,913 --> 00:53:38,415
What do we do here?

1071
00:53:38,415 --> 00:53:39,916
- I don't know
- Let's wait at our seats.

1072
00:53:39,916 --> 00:53:41,418
[Let Us Explain Our Service
To Our First Guests]

1073
00:53:41,418 --> 00:53:42,519
Look at that table.

1074
00:53:42,519 --> 00:53:44,221
- Hello.
- Hello.

1075
00:53:44,221 --> 00:53:46,590
Gosh, he brought towels.

1076
00:53:46,590 --> 00:53:48,258
It's served very neatly.

1077
00:53:48,258 --> 00:53:49,359
This is very nice.

1078
00:53:49,359 --> 00:53:52,462
- It's so nice and warm.
- It's warm.

1079
00:53:52,462 --> 00:53:54,197
There's even a magnifying glass.

1080
00:53:54,197 --> 00:53:55,799
Let's see what they have.

1081
00:53:55,799 --> 00:53:57,467
The font is nice and large.

1082
00:53:57,467 --> 00:53:59,803
[A Menu In Big Bold Print]

1083
00:53:59,803 --> 00:54:02,272
[A Magnifying Glass To Get A Closer Look]

1084
00:54:02,272 --> 00:54:06,309
[Orders Taken At Your Table]
We have orange, lemon, and honey tea.

1085
00:54:06,309 --> 00:54:08,445
That one's nice. We also have chamomile.

1086
00:54:09,079 --> 00:54:10,881
Should we have something sweet?

1087
00:54:10,881 --> 00:54:12,215
You had breakfast, right?

1088
00:54:12,215 --> 00:54:13,784
- Yes.
- Yes, we did.

1089
00:54:13,784 --> 00:54:16,186
- We had lunch.
- Then we went straight to work.

1090
00:54:16,186 --> 00:54:18,021
You're very hardworking.

1091
00:54:19,589 --> 00:54:21,324
- Take your time deciding.
- Okay.

1092
00:54:21,324 --> 00:54:22,893
- Take a look.
- Let me take a look.

1093
00:54:22,893 --> 00:54:24,894
- Americano?
- Someone is coming.

1094
00:54:25,996 --> 00:54:27,230
Don't we need one each?

1095
00:54:27,230 --> 00:54:28,398
[The Second Customers Of The Day]

1096
00:54:28,398 --> 00:54:29,666
Hello!

1097
00:54:29,666 --> 00:54:31,301
Hello.

1098
00:54:31,301 --> 00:54:33,236
- Table for two?
- Yes.

1099
00:54:33,236 --> 00:54:35,005
They're from Singi Village.

1100
00:54:35,005 --> 00:54:36,440
- Hello.
- Hello.

1101
00:54:36,440 --> 00:54:38,809
- Hello.
- They're from Singi Village.

1102
00:54:38,809 --> 00:54:41,745
They recently moved to Singi Village.

1103
00:54:41,745 --> 00:54:42,913
It's French.

1104
00:54:42,913 --> 00:54:45,849
Apparently, "bonjour" means hello.

1105
00:54:46,750 --> 00:54:49,086
- What shall we eat?
- What about you?

1106
00:54:49,086 --> 00:54:50,320
[Menu]

1107
00:54:50,320 --> 00:54:52,923
They have sweet potato cake.

1108
00:54:52,923 --> 00:54:55,359
[The Flavor Is Predictable,
Given The Familiar Ingredients]

1109
00:54:55,359 --> 00:54:56,393
"Green barley field."

1110
00:54:56,393 --> 00:54:58,595
I left my key in the engine.

1111
00:54:58,595 --> 00:55:00,731
Is that why the door wouldn't open?

1112
00:55:00,731 --> 00:55:03,100
My mind keeps wandering.

1113
00:55:03,100 --> 00:55:04,201
It happens to all of us.

1114
00:55:04,201 --> 00:55:05,335
[No Idea What That Is]
[Moving On]

1115
00:55:05,335 --> 00:55:07,404
- This is hard.
- Are you getting the same thing?

1116
00:55:07,404 --> 00:55:09,039
We'll go with whatever you pick.

1117
00:55:09,039 --> 00:55:10,774
My arm here...

1118
00:55:10,774 --> 00:55:13,777
My arm won't reach out all the way.

1119
00:55:13,777 --> 00:55:15,679
- Should we try that?
- The Bonjour...

1120
00:55:15,679 --> 00:55:18,248
- I've never tried it.
- Let's try it since it's new.

1121
00:55:18,248 --> 00:55:20,016
- Tell me when you're ready.
- We're ready.

1122
00:55:20,016 --> 00:55:22,185
- Have you decided?
- What is all this?

1123
00:55:22,185 --> 00:55:24,020
- Americano.
- We also have teas.

1124
00:55:24,020 --> 00:55:25,889
- What is an Americano?
- It's coffee.

1125
00:55:25,889 --> 00:55:27,758
- It's a coffee?
- Yes.

1126
00:55:27,758 --> 00:55:29,259
Are these two different?

1127
00:55:29,259 --> 00:55:31,733
- Have it with cake.
- Let's try.

1128
00:55:31,733 --> 00:55:35,032
[Waiting For The Chance
To Jump In And Explain]

1129
00:55:35,032 --> 00:55:36,066
Iced America?

1130
00:55:36,066 --> 00:55:37,400
- Try it.
- Okay, Americano.

1131
00:55:37,400 --> 00:55:38,735
- We'll have four.
- Hot or cold?

1132
00:55:38,735 --> 00:55:39,769
- Warm.
- Warm.

1133
00:55:39,769 --> 00:55:41,438
- Warm one?
- Yes.

1134
00:55:41,438 --> 00:55:43,106
We'll also have this.

1135
00:55:43,106 --> 00:55:44,775
- Crème brûlée?
- Yes.

1136
00:55:44,775 --> 00:55:46,109
Do you just need one?

1137
00:55:46,109 --> 00:55:48,779
- How big is one?
- Oh, right.

1138
00:55:48,779 --> 00:55:51,648
- I'll show you.
- Okay.

1139
00:55:51,648 --> 00:55:54,417
[Off To See The Crème Brûlée]

1140
00:55:54,417 --> 00:55:55,919
It's this size.

1141
00:55:55,919 --> 00:55:57,620
[Crème Brûlée]
Just one.

1142
00:56:00,290 --> 00:56:01,958
We'll take one each.

1143
00:56:01,958 --> 00:56:03,460
One for each person? Four in total?

1144
00:56:03,460 --> 00:56:04,928
- Would you like four?
- Yes.

1145
00:56:04,928 --> 00:56:06,163
Okay.

1146
00:56:06,163 --> 00:56:07,664
You made an excellent choice.

1147
00:56:07,664 --> 00:56:09,065
[4 Hot Americanos, 4 Crème Brûlée]

1148
00:56:09,466 --> 00:56:12,202
[The Crème Brûlée Is An Excellent Choice!]

1149
00:56:12,202 --> 00:56:15,172
[A Fragrant Vanilla Bean Base]

1150
00:56:15,172 --> 00:56:17,707
[With A Dash Of The Chef's Flair]

1151
00:56:17,707 --> 00:56:19,209
[Baked In A Water Bath For 30 Minutes]

1152
00:56:19,209 --> 00:56:21,070
[Cooled In The Fridge For 1 Hour]

1153
00:56:23,013 --> 00:56:24,251
Oh, the scale.

1154
00:56:24,251 --> 00:56:28,435
[It Had Enough Time
For The Flavor To Deepen]

1155
00:56:30,357 --> 00:56:32,517
[A Spoonful Of Sugar On Top]

1156
00:56:34,658 --> 00:56:37,060
[Sprinkle It Evenly With Light Taps]

1157
00:56:37,060 --> 00:56:39,296
[Then Dust Off The Rest]

1158
00:56:39,296 --> 00:56:40,363
- It's done.
- Okay.

1159
00:56:40,363 --> 00:56:42,532
[And]

1160
00:56:43,200 --> 00:56:45,473
[Firearm Locked And Loaded]

1161
00:56:46,903 --> 00:56:49,602
[A Crispy Caramel Coating]

1162
00:56:59,082 --> 00:57:00,784
It looks great.

1163
00:57:00,784 --> 00:57:02,118
I think it looks good.

1164
00:57:02,118 --> 00:57:03,453
- Hold on.
- Okay.

1165
00:57:03,453 --> 00:57:06,356
Why don't we serve this with rice?

1166
00:57:06,356 --> 00:57:08,157
And some kimchi.

1167
00:57:08,992 --> 00:57:10,060
That way...

1168
00:57:10,060 --> 00:57:12,432
[We'll Serve It With Coffee]

1169
00:57:14,631 --> 00:57:16,733
[Day One Of Barista Training]

1170
00:57:16,733 --> 00:57:18,735
You're doing a good job.

1171
00:57:19,836 --> 00:57:22,972
I'm doing it step by step,
just like Seon Ho taught me.

1172
00:57:23,440 --> 00:57:25,508
[Grinding The Coffee Beans]

1173
00:57:25,508 --> 00:57:27,644
[Shot Glass At The Ready]

1174
00:57:27,644 --> 00:57:29,750
[Mug Also At The Ready]

1175
00:57:32,349 --> 00:57:33,917
[Shot Extracted]

1176
00:57:33,917 --> 00:57:36,019
[Draw The Hot Water First]

1177
00:57:36,019 --> 00:57:38,154
[Extract The Next Shot]

1178
00:57:38,154 --> 00:57:40,357
[Wipe The Extra Tampers]

1179
00:57:40,357 --> 00:57:42,859
[There Are Two Types Of People
In This World]

1180
00:57:42,859 --> 00:57:45,629
[Pro Multitaskers]

1181
00:57:45,629 --> 00:57:49,209
[And Kim Hee Ae]

1182
00:57:54,871 --> 00:57:56,837
[One Crème Brûlée]

1183
00:57:59,276 --> 00:58:01,342
[Two]

1184
00:58:02,279 --> 00:58:04,499
[Three...]

1185
00:58:06,816 --> 00:58:09,009
[Four!]

1186
00:58:09,753 --> 00:58:12,255
[We Can't Carry These All At Once]

1187
00:58:12,255 --> 00:58:14,868
[So We'll Use A Silver Tray]

1188
00:58:19,863 --> 00:58:21,598
All four coffees are ready to go.

1189
00:58:21,598 --> 00:58:22,999
Okay.

1190
00:58:24,601 --> 00:58:25,835
Here they come.

1191
00:58:25,835 --> 00:58:27,437
[Our Graceful Server]

1192
00:58:27,437 --> 00:58:29,272
That's pretty small.

1193
00:58:29,272 --> 00:58:30,941
When would we ever try this?

1194
00:58:30,941 --> 00:58:32,242
She...

1195
00:58:32,242 --> 00:58:34,362
- This is such an honor.
- It's not very sweet, right?

1196
00:58:35,512 --> 00:58:38,614
They served it hot and fresh.

1197
00:58:42,018 --> 00:58:43,320
The cream is cold.

1198
00:58:43,320 --> 00:58:45,755
- It's cold?
- Yes, it's cold.

1199
00:58:45,755 --> 00:58:48,825
It looks like soup.
I wonder if it tastes like it.

1200
00:58:52,729 --> 00:58:55,565
I don't know how to eat this
since I'm just a country boy.

1201
00:58:55,565 --> 00:58:58,068
- This is a first.
- It's warm.

1202
00:58:58,068 --> 00:58:59,903
- You just eat it?
- Yes.

1203
00:58:59,903 --> 00:59:02,572
It's nice if you have it with the coffee.

1204
00:59:03,040 --> 00:59:04,274
Just pour it in the coffee.

1205
00:59:04,274 --> 00:59:06,409
I told my son...

1206
00:59:06,409 --> 00:59:08,235
[Takes One Bite]

1207
00:59:08,778 --> 00:59:10,179
That's it.

1208
00:59:10,613 --> 00:59:11,679
[Slurp]

1209
00:59:12,749 --> 00:59:13,984
[Dessert Card]

1210
00:59:13,984 --> 00:59:16,652
It's made with milk.

1211
00:59:17,253 --> 00:59:20,357
"It's made with eggs and milk,

1212
00:59:20,357 --> 00:59:23,226
creating a creamy, velvety...

1213
00:59:23,226 --> 00:59:24,211
[Gulp]

1214
00:59:24,828 --> 00:59:27,330
dessert.

1215
00:59:28,335 --> 00:59:30,853
[The Crème Brûlée]
[A Dessert That Looks Like Soup]

1216
00:59:31,935 --> 00:59:33,670
[Use Your Spoon]

1217
00:59:33,670 --> 00:59:36,219
[To Crack The Crispy, Warm Top Layer]

1218
00:59:37,774 --> 00:59:39,654
[To Get The Sweet Vanilla Cream Filling]

1219
00:59:46,516 --> 00:59:48,284
[A New Sense Of Joy]

1220
00:59:48,284 --> 00:59:52,694
[From New And Unfamiliar Flavors]

1221
01:00:00,430 --> 01:00:02,710
[Slurping Down Americano]

1222
01:00:05,902 --> 01:00:06,903
- It's refreshing.
- It is.

1223
01:00:06,903 --> 01:00:08,289
[Sneaking A Glance]

1224
01:00:08,872 --> 01:00:11,212
[Sneaking A Taste]

1225
01:00:15,745 --> 01:00:17,265
Is it sweet?

1226
01:00:17,265 --> 01:00:18,348
Is it not sweet?

1227
01:00:18,348 --> 01:00:20,884
It's bitter.

1228
01:00:20,884 --> 01:00:22,685
[Spooning A Taste]

1229
01:00:22,685 --> 01:00:23,920
I'll just drink it.

1230
01:00:23,920 --> 01:00:26,223
It's nice and refreshing.

1231
01:00:26,223 --> 01:00:27,223
[Looks Around]

1232
01:00:27,223 --> 01:00:29,759
- It's okay. I won't finish it.
- No.

1233
01:00:29,759 --> 01:00:32,195
I won't eat it all.

1234
01:00:32,195 --> 01:00:34,898
- Do I put this in here?
- That's not it.

1235
01:00:34,898 --> 01:00:36,032
[Temporarily Detained]

1236
01:00:36,032 --> 01:00:37,400
Should I make it sweeter?

1237
01:00:37,400 --> 01:00:39,402
Would you like it sweeter, ma'am?

1238
01:00:39,402 --> 01:00:40,937
She took a sip and said it was too bitter.

1239
01:00:40,937 --> 01:00:43,473
The rest of us like it.

1240
01:00:43,473 --> 01:00:45,466
[Adding Sweet Syrup]

1241
01:00:46,810 --> 01:00:49,379
[The Oldest Daughter Doppelganger
To The Rescue]

1242
01:00:49,379 --> 01:00:51,414
Oh, my.

1243
01:00:51,414 --> 01:00:53,416
I caused you trouble.

1244
01:00:53,416 --> 01:00:56,486
Why does she keep bringing us stuff?

1245
01:00:56,486 --> 01:00:57,821
She's bringing us tasty treats.

1246
01:00:57,821 --> 01:01:00,256
Can you afford it?

1247
01:01:00,256 --> 01:01:02,792
No, I can't. So, give me money.

1248
01:01:06,096 --> 01:01:07,564
There's something in the corner.

1249
01:01:07,564 --> 01:01:10,033
[After Taking A Sip Of
The Sweetened Americano]

1250
01:01:10,033 --> 01:01:12,063
[She Digs Into The Crème Brûlée]

1251
01:01:14,324 --> 01:01:15,409
[Pleased]

1252
01:01:15,409 --> 01:01:16,838
[Slurp]

1253
01:01:18,274 --> 01:01:19,327
[Hit The Spot]

1254
01:01:20,176 --> 01:01:23,846
It's sweet and bitter,
so it's well balanced.

1255
01:01:24,581 --> 01:01:26,916
[Meanwhile At The Singi Villagers' Table]

1256
01:01:26,916 --> 01:01:29,519
Let's have an Americano.

1257
01:01:30,220 --> 01:01:32,422
We'll have two Americanos.

1258
01:01:32,422 --> 01:01:33,556
- Would you like it hot?
- Yes.

1259
01:01:33,556 --> 01:01:35,258
[2 Hot Americanos]

1260
01:01:35,258 --> 01:01:36,292
I'll treat you.

1261
01:01:36,292 --> 01:01:37,560
[We'll Have This Dessert!]

1262
01:01:37,560 --> 01:01:38,862
- Bonjour Barley Tart?
- Yes.

1263
01:01:38,862 --> 01:01:41,197
One Bonjour Green Barley Tart.

1264
01:01:41,197 --> 01:01:43,266
Thank you.

1265
01:01:45,502 --> 01:01:48,404
This will do for lunch.

1266
01:01:50,974 --> 01:01:52,475
[The Star Backdrop Of Our Bakery]

1267
01:01:52,475 --> 01:01:55,211
[And The Emblem Of Gapyeong Village]

1268
01:01:55,211 --> 01:01:56,821
[The Green Barley Field]

1269
01:01:58,314 --> 01:02:00,727
[We Made A Dessert That Captured]
[Its Radiance And Fragrance]

1270
01:02:06,089 --> 01:02:08,495
[Bonjour Green Barley Field Tart]

1271
01:02:08,958 --> 01:02:10,760
[Green Barley Monte Cream]

1272
01:02:10,760 --> 01:02:11,961
[Atop The Rippling Monte Cream]

1273
01:02:11,961 --> 01:02:14,100
[Canola Buds Are Planted]

1274
01:02:15,064 --> 01:02:17,624
[To Evoke The Green Barley Field]
[Budding In The Spring]

1275
01:02:18,334 --> 01:02:22,238
[Elegantly Dried Buds]
[Placed Atop Sweet Lemon Cream]

1276
01:02:24,507 --> 01:02:26,843
[To Evoke The Sunny Canola Flower Fields]
[That Light Up The Village]

1277
01:02:26,843 --> 01:02:29,078
[Atop A Trail Of Sprinkled Crumble]

1278
01:02:29,812 --> 01:02:33,172
[Sits A Fragrant Mugwort Sponge Cake]

1279
01:02:34,918 --> 01:02:37,298
[Evoking The High Peaks]
[Of Bangjang Mountain]

1280
01:02:42,992 --> 01:02:44,845
[What Is This Dessert Called?]

1281
01:02:45,228 --> 01:02:46,329
Action!

1282
01:02:46,329 --> 01:02:50,133
Bonjour Tart Green Barley Field!

1283
01:02:50,133 --> 01:02:51,467
[Bonjour Tart Green Barley Field!]

1284
01:02:51,467 --> 01:02:54,370
- You did so well.
- Thank you.

1285
01:02:54,370 --> 01:02:55,505
[Bonjour Green Barley Field Tart!]

1286
01:02:55,505 --> 01:02:58,205
- Ki Taek, reset the scale to zero.
- Okay.

1287
01:03:02,745 --> 01:03:04,981
[Green Barley Ganache]

1288
01:03:04,981 --> 01:03:06,583
[The Crust Is Made Of Butter And Flour
That Cradles The Filling]

1289
01:03:06,583 --> 01:03:08,422
[Adds A Buttery Richness And Delicate Crispness]

1290
01:03:08,422 --> 01:03:10,429
[The Tart Should Be Filled With
Green Barley Cream But...]

1291
01:03:11,020 --> 01:03:13,329
[Too Thick]

1292
01:03:15,158 --> 01:03:16,926
It's too thick.

1293
01:03:16,926 --> 01:03:19,596
It's thicker than before.

1294
01:03:19,596 --> 01:03:21,764
I don't think this will work.

1295
01:03:22,732 --> 01:03:24,902
[A Month Earlier]

1296
01:03:24,902 --> 01:03:26,942
[The Same Thing Happened]

1297
01:03:28,738 --> 01:03:30,974
This isn't working.

1298
01:03:30,974 --> 01:03:33,443
- It has a thick consistency.
- Yes, you're right.

1299
01:03:33,443 --> 01:03:37,180
- You need to press it against the base.
- Oh, it needs to touch the base.

1300
01:03:37,180 --> 01:03:41,584
You can just spread it out like this.

1301
01:03:46,623 --> 01:03:48,458
This... Wait a minute.

1302
01:03:48,458 --> 01:03:50,026
Okay, hang on.

1303
01:03:51,894 --> 01:03:53,320
[Naturally Hands Over The Spoon]

1304
01:04:02,672 --> 01:04:05,808
- Okay, reset it to zero.
- Okay.

1305
01:04:10,680 --> 01:04:12,980
[Citron Filling]

1306
01:04:18,221 --> 01:04:19,722
[Checking The Scale As He Goes]

1307
01:04:19,722 --> 01:04:21,424
One more.

1308
01:04:23,493 --> 01:04:26,029
[The Exact Amount Is A Trade Secret]

1309
01:04:26,029 --> 01:04:27,363
Zero.

1310
01:04:28,131 --> 01:04:29,465
- Here you go.
- Okay.

1311
01:04:29,465 --> 01:04:31,305
[This One First]

1312
01:04:39,976 --> 01:04:43,402
[The Crust Is Filled To The Top
With Green Barley Cream]

1313
01:04:57,527 --> 01:05:00,713
[Smoothing The Filling]

1314
01:05:27,290 --> 01:05:30,156
[The Truth Behind
Bonjour Green Barley Field Tart]

1315
01:05:30,960 --> 01:05:33,526
[It Was Extremely Stressful]

1316
01:05:34,597 --> 01:05:37,503
[As Beautiful As It Was,
The Process Was Very Complex]

1317
01:05:39,469 --> 01:05:40,803
- The base.
- Yes.

1318
01:05:40,803 --> 01:05:42,338
We're going to make this part.

1319
01:05:42,338 --> 01:05:44,740
- The base of the Green Barley Field Tart.
- Yes.

1320
01:05:54,484 --> 01:05:56,485
- Ki Taek, put it in.
- Okay.

1321
01:06:01,391 --> 01:06:04,193
[It Had To Be Built From Scratch]

1322
01:06:04,193 --> 01:06:08,799
[With Four Different Types Of Cream]

1323
01:06:11,834 --> 01:06:13,035
Okay.

1324
01:06:13,035 --> 01:06:15,838
It's 60 degrees.
It's gone down to 57 degrees.

1325
01:06:15,838 --> 01:06:19,338
[On Top Of The Complex Tart Crust Process]

1326
01:06:20,343 --> 01:06:23,729
[Comes The Final Decorating Step]

1327
01:06:25,415 --> 01:06:27,921
[Green Barley Cream]

1328
01:06:32,755 --> 01:06:36,623
[Ki Taek's In Charge Of
The Canola Flowers And Buds]

1329
01:06:45,601 --> 01:06:48,334
[Lemon Cream]

1330
01:07:05,488 --> 01:07:07,761
[Green Barley Powder]

1331
01:07:09,091 --> 01:07:11,324
[The Mountain-Shaped Sponge Cake]

1332
01:07:14,864 --> 01:07:17,210
[Almond Crumble]

1333
01:07:25,341 --> 01:07:27,654
[Green Barley Ganache]

1334
01:07:45,962 --> 01:07:48,748
[Canola Flower Petals]

1335
01:07:53,302 --> 01:07:55,882
[Canola Flower Buds]

1336
01:07:59,008 --> 01:08:01,161
[Finishing Touches With Gold]

1337
01:08:10,219 --> 01:08:13,656
[Bonjour Green Barley Field
Is Ready To Be Served!]

1338
01:08:13,656 --> 01:08:15,958
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

1339
01:08:15,958 --> 01:08:18,127
Thank you.

1340
01:08:19,328 --> 01:08:21,130
It's very pretty.

1341
01:08:24,133 --> 01:08:26,469
[After Cutting The Tart Into Bite-Sized Chunks]

1342
01:08:26,469 --> 01:08:29,972
[You Have The First Bite, Dear]

1343
01:08:33,943 --> 01:08:36,345
- It's so tasty!
- Is it?

1344
01:08:43,452 --> 01:08:47,356
You can't get this anywhere else.
It's really delicious.

1345
01:08:48,691 --> 01:08:51,160
We'll be eating this all day.

1346
01:08:51,160 --> 01:08:54,563
It's meant to be enjoyed
while having light conversation.

1347
01:08:54,964 --> 01:08:56,132
[Scraping The Crumbs]

1348
01:08:56,132 --> 01:08:59,201
[If You Still Don't Feel Satisfied]

1349
01:08:59,201 --> 01:09:00,436
We are in our 60s.

1350
01:09:00,436 --> 01:09:02,138
[Feel Free To Pick Up The Entire Bowl]

1351
01:09:02,138 --> 01:09:03,406
You finished it off like that?

1352
01:09:03,406 --> 01:09:04,473
Eat every last bit.

1353
01:09:04,473 --> 01:09:06,575
- I ate it all.
- We...

1354
01:09:09,812 --> 01:09:11,480
You need to clean the plate.

1355
01:09:11,480 --> 01:09:15,017
Scrape up every last crumb.

1356
01:09:16,619 --> 01:09:18,487
[Polishing It Off]

1357
01:09:18,487 --> 01:09:20,389
Is someone after your food?

1358
01:09:22,858 --> 01:09:25,928
There's no need to keep it at the table.
You should eat it up.

1359
01:09:28,064 --> 01:09:32,301
Thank you so much
for being our first customers.

1360
01:09:32,301 --> 01:09:36,339
She called us as soon as it opened.
She was like, "Let's go!"

1361
01:09:36,339 --> 01:09:39,542
We're just country folks,
so all of these are new to us.

1362
01:09:39,542 --> 01:09:45,681
My son told me to check out this bakery
that has delicious food.

1363
01:09:46,115 --> 01:09:47,783
- Your son?
- He lives in Seoul.

1364
01:09:47,783 --> 01:09:50,820
- From Seoul?
- Yes, he came to visit.

1365
01:09:50,820 --> 01:09:52,588
[Meanwhile]

1366
01:09:52,588 --> 01:09:56,014
[First Break In 3 Hours At The Tart Station]

1367
01:09:57,860 --> 01:10:00,997
Green Barley Field Tart is all the rage.

1368
01:10:00,997 --> 01:10:03,265
- Do you want me to make more?
- They said it's delicious.

1369
01:10:03,265 --> 01:10:06,035
- I just came to pass on the message.
- Did you?

1370
01:10:06,035 --> 01:10:07,136
Make one more, please.

1371
01:10:07,136 --> 01:10:09,705
Tell them to stop eating.

1372
01:10:11,540 --> 01:10:13,942
Hurry up and get to it.

1373
01:10:15,277 --> 01:10:17,279
- Goodbye.
- Thank you.

1374
01:10:17,279 --> 01:10:19,281
- Take care.
- Okay.

1375
01:10:20,031 --> 01:10:21,584
Yes, goodbye.

1376
01:10:21,584 --> 01:10:23,753
You dropped this, ma'am. The card.

1377
01:10:23,753 --> 01:10:24,740
[Crème Brûlée Dessert Card]

1378
01:10:24,740 --> 01:10:26,522
Oh, gosh.

1379
01:10:26,522 --> 01:10:28,424
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

1380
01:10:33,162 --> 01:10:35,164
They scraped it clean.

1381
01:10:35,164 --> 01:10:36,899
I know, right?

1382
01:10:37,567 --> 01:10:41,570
You did great.
You handled six coffee orders really fast.

1383
01:10:41,570 --> 01:10:43,606
- My hands were shaking.
- Really?

1384
01:10:43,606 --> 01:10:46,509
That's understandable.

1385
01:10:46,509 --> 01:10:48,911
My goodness. But I knew you'd do well.

1386
01:10:48,911 --> 01:10:50,980
People who are good at one thing

1387
01:10:50,980 --> 01:10:53,516
- tend to be good at everything else.
- Thank you.

1388
01:10:53,516 --> 01:10:55,250
I love to see it.

1389
01:10:56,085 --> 01:10:58,220
- I think this whole team is great.
- You think so?

1390
01:10:58,220 --> 01:10:59,255
Thank you.

1391
01:10:59,255 --> 01:11:00,956
It's a well-oiled machine.

1392
01:11:04,160 --> 01:11:07,096
How long have you been in this business?

1393
01:11:07,096 --> 01:11:08,698
We debuted in 2015.

1394
01:11:08,698 --> 01:11:10,132
- The year 2015?
- Yes.

1395
01:11:10,132 --> 01:11:12,234
You must have been a trainee before that.

1396
01:11:12,234 --> 01:11:14,270
Oh, my training started in 2012.

1397
01:11:14,270 --> 01:11:16,539
- My goodness.
- I debuted after that period of training.

1398
01:11:16,539 --> 01:11:17,807
You trained for three years?

1399
01:11:17,807 --> 01:11:19,875
Yes, that's about right.

1400
01:11:20,409 --> 01:11:22,745
I hope our group can perform
for many years to come.

1401
01:11:22,745 --> 01:11:25,681
That's one of my biggest concerns.

1402
01:11:25,681 --> 01:11:27,349
Why's that?

1403
01:11:27,349 --> 01:11:29,618
When I look at people like you,
who have a lifetime of experience,

1404
01:11:29,618 --> 01:11:31,052
I feel so in awe.

1405
01:11:31,052 --> 01:11:32,121
People like me...

1406
01:11:32,121 --> 01:11:34,590
But you can make it as well.

1407
01:11:34,590 --> 01:11:36,525
- You think so?
- Yes.

1408
01:11:36,525 --> 01:11:38,160
Sorry, can I ask how old you are?

1409
01:11:38,160 --> 01:11:39,628
I'm 28 years old.

1410
01:11:39,628 --> 01:11:40,963
What year were you born?

1411
01:11:40,963 --> 01:11:42,865
- In 1999.
- Oh, right.

1412
01:11:43,332 --> 01:11:44,400
- Oh, gosh.
- How?

1413
01:11:44,400 --> 01:11:46,168
You could be my son.

1414
01:11:47,203 --> 01:11:48,771
- Mom.
- Yes, I may as well be.

1415
01:11:48,771 --> 01:11:49,739
Mom!

1416
01:11:49,739 --> 01:11:54,025
[While The Hall Team
Gets To Know Each Other]

1417
01:11:56,078 --> 01:11:59,604
[Someone Wants To Know More
About Bonjour Bakery]

1418
01:12:02,585 --> 01:12:04,153
- Welcome!
- Hello.

1419
01:12:04,153 --> 01:12:05,354
- Hello.
- Hi.

1420
01:12:05,354 --> 01:12:06,689
- Are you here alone?
- Yes.

1421
01:12:06,689 --> 01:12:08,758
Please sit wherever you like.

1422
01:12:08,758 --> 01:12:10,259
Where would you recommend?

1423
01:12:11,260 --> 01:12:13,395
Why don't you sit by the window?

1424
01:12:13,395 --> 01:12:14,796
It's nice and cool.

1425
01:12:17,900 --> 01:12:20,269
[He Strolled In But...]

1426
01:12:20,269 --> 01:12:23,272
[Lee Sang Yeol]

1427
01:12:31,313 --> 01:12:33,149
Are you the actress Kim Hee Ae?

1428
01:12:33,149 --> 01:12:34,883
Yes, I am.

1429
01:12:36,085 --> 01:12:38,820
I saw online that you're also a professor.

1430
01:12:39,789 --> 01:12:41,590
- That's old news.
- What?

1431
01:12:41,590 --> 01:12:43,259
That's in the past.

1432
01:12:43,259 --> 01:12:45,394
That's what I read online.

1433
01:12:45,394 --> 01:12:48,664
That was over 20 years ago.

1434
01:12:51,233 --> 01:12:55,270
[Staring At The Menu For A Long Time]

1435
01:12:58,474 --> 01:12:59,909
Give me whatever.

1436
01:12:59,909 --> 01:13:01,310
What would you like?

1437
01:13:03,412 --> 01:13:04,814
- Americano?
- Capo...

1438
01:13:04,814 --> 01:13:06,048
- Cappuccino?
- Yes.

1439
01:13:06,048 --> 01:13:07,583
You mean coffee with cream, right?

1440
01:13:07,583 --> 01:13:09,885
- No, I don't want cream.
- Just...

1441
01:13:09,885 --> 01:13:12,354
- Just plain black coffee?
- Yes.

1442
01:13:12,354 --> 01:13:15,424
- Would you like a hot or iced Americano?
- Hot.

1443
01:13:15,424 --> 01:13:16,525
- Hot?
- Yeah.

1444
01:13:16,525 --> 01:13:19,127
- You don't want anything to eat?
- Hold on.

1445
01:13:19,695 --> 01:13:21,397
[Bonjour Green Barley Field Tart]
This one's popular.

1446
01:13:21,397 --> 01:13:24,333
It's our tastiest signature menu.

1447
01:13:27,469 --> 01:13:29,038
I'll try one.

1448
01:13:29,038 --> 01:13:30,439
- Would you like this one?
- Yes.

1449
01:13:30,439 --> 01:13:31,907
All right.

1450
01:13:33,275 --> 01:13:35,678
What made you come here on your own?

1451
01:13:35,678 --> 01:13:37,980
I don't have anyone to come with.

1452
01:13:37,980 --> 01:13:40,516
- That's why you're here alone?
- Yes.

1453
01:13:40,516 --> 01:13:41,817
- It's good you came.
- What?

1454
01:13:41,817 --> 01:13:43,152
It's good that you came.

1455
01:13:43,152 --> 01:13:46,155
It's healing to have coffee alone.

1456
01:13:46,155 --> 01:13:48,924
Having some time to yourself.

1457
01:13:48,924 --> 01:13:52,361
- You must be over 65 to come in here.
- Yes?

1458
01:13:52,361 --> 01:13:55,531
I need to check your ID.
It's required by regulation.

1459
01:13:55,531 --> 01:13:57,733
- Are you sure you're over 65?
- Well...

1460
01:13:57,733 --> 01:14:00,169
- Aren't you just 60 years old?
- Oh, please.

1461
01:14:00,169 --> 01:14:01,503
I'm over 70 years old.

1462
01:14:01,503 --> 01:14:03,272
- Are you really?
- Yes.

1463
01:14:03,272 --> 01:14:06,108
You look so much younger.

1464
01:14:06,108 --> 01:14:08,377
I don't believe it.

1465
01:14:10,813 --> 01:14:13,148
Hold on while we get your order ready.

1466
01:14:17,386 --> 01:14:19,555
[While The Coffee Is Getting Made]

1467
01:14:19,555 --> 01:14:21,292
[In The Green Barley Station]

1468
01:14:27,830 --> 01:14:29,231
Oh, right.

1469
01:14:31,867 --> 01:14:35,142
[He Folds His Pesky Long Arm
To Keep It Out Of The Way]

1470
01:14:43,913 --> 01:14:46,819
[When His Arm Starts Cramping]

1471
01:14:47,783 --> 01:14:49,718
[He Bends It The Other Way]

1472
01:14:49,718 --> 01:14:52,187
- You're completing these so quickly.
- What?

1473
01:14:52,187 --> 01:14:53,956
You've gotten so fast at this.

1474
01:14:53,956 --> 01:14:55,858
I'm not giving it my all.

1475
01:14:55,858 --> 01:14:57,526
But it looks really good.

1476
01:14:57,526 --> 01:15:00,462
You say that,
but I know you did your best.

1477
01:15:01,196 --> 01:15:03,165
It's ready.

1478
01:15:03,699 --> 01:15:05,967
- Here's your coffee.
- Thank you.

1479
01:15:06,702 --> 01:15:09,738
[1 Hot Americano]

1480
01:15:09,738 --> 01:15:11,106
[Scratches]

1481
01:15:21,116 --> 01:15:24,042
[Please Wait A Moment]

1482
01:15:25,421 --> 01:15:28,854
[It Tastes Better With The Dessert]

1483
01:15:29,425 --> 01:15:31,360
Here's your Green Barley Tart.

1484
01:15:31,360 --> 01:15:34,129
[1 Bonjour Green Barley Field Tart]

1485
01:15:34,129 --> 01:15:35,764
This is a description card.

1486
01:15:35,764 --> 01:15:37,499
If you read it while you eat,

1487
01:15:37,499 --> 01:15:39,534
it can make the dessert more enjoyable.

1488
01:15:41,971 --> 01:15:43,772
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

1489
01:15:58,120 --> 01:16:01,123
[He Stares At The Unusual Dessert]

1490
01:16:01,123 --> 01:16:05,129
[While Sipping Away At His Coffee]

1491
01:16:20,142 --> 01:16:21,510
[Eventually]

1492
01:16:21,510 --> 01:16:22,845
[After A Few More Sips]

1493
01:16:22,845 --> 01:16:24,246
[Just Sipping Away]

1494
01:16:24,246 --> 01:16:26,218
[At His Coffee]

1495
01:16:34,790 --> 01:16:38,203
[He Cautiously Pulls The Dessert Close]

1496
01:16:39,862 --> 01:16:41,888
[Hesitant]

1497
01:16:54,576 --> 01:16:57,436
[He Cautiously Takes Another Bite]

1498
01:17:18,267 --> 01:17:21,700
[It Quickly Grows On Him]

1499
01:17:32,119 --> 01:17:36,051
[Thanks To The Small Courage
To Overcome Hesitation]

1500
01:17:36,051 --> 01:17:40,807
[A Small Thrill Came With The New Taste]

1501
01:17:45,260 --> 01:17:50,068
[Picks Up The Rest
And Finishes It Off Like A Cookie]

1502
01:17:57,139 --> 01:17:59,239
[Last Piece]

1503
01:18:03,779 --> 01:18:05,052
[A Quick Wipe]

1504
01:18:20,596 --> 01:18:24,089
[An Unfamiliar Start]

1505
01:18:25,200 --> 01:18:29,568
[Led To A Taste Of Sweet Delight]

1506
01:18:31,940 --> 01:18:34,143
- I want to go check it out.
- This should be fun.

1507
01:18:34,143 --> 01:18:37,479
[It's Suddenly Rowdy Outside]

1508
01:18:37,479 --> 01:18:38,647
Let's go together.

1509
01:18:38,647 --> 01:18:40,082
I don't think we're allowed.

1510
01:18:40,082 --> 01:18:41,717
It says you need to be over 65.

1511
01:18:41,717 --> 01:18:42,851
Sir.

1512
01:18:42,851 --> 01:18:45,020
- Hello!
- Welcome.

1513
01:18:45,020 --> 01:18:46,922
Oh, but...

1514
01:18:46,922 --> 01:18:48,423
What a shame.

1515
01:18:49,124 --> 01:18:50,192
[It's A Senior Café]

1516
01:18:50,192 --> 01:18:51,627
[But A Crowd Of Children Has Arrived]

1517
01:18:51,627 --> 01:18:53,562
- Hello.
- Hello.

1518
01:18:53,562 --> 01:18:55,664
[Even At A Glance]
Are you here alone?

1519
01:18:55,664 --> 01:18:58,410
[They Are Clearly All Younger Than 65]

1520
01:18:59,468 --> 01:19:01,703
The kids probably want to eat it.
What do we do?

1521
01:19:01,703 --> 01:19:02,871
I know, right?

1522
01:19:02,871 --> 01:19:04,172
I feel so bad.

1523
01:19:07,743 --> 01:19:10,049
[You Must Be Over 65 Years Old To Enter]

1524
01:19:16,857 --> 01:19:22,090
[The Voices Of The Customers]

1525
01:19:22,090 --> 01:19:24,426
[How Did You Come To Visit?]
She said, "It's called Bonjour Bakery."

1526
01:19:24,426 --> 01:19:27,596
I said, "Does that mean
Director Bong Joon Ho will be there?

1527
01:19:27,596 --> 01:19:30,098
She said, "I don't know."

1528
01:19:30,098 --> 01:19:32,768
I heard an actor is coming.
What was his name?

1529
01:19:32,768 --> 01:19:35,470
Cha Tae Won or something.

1530
01:19:35,470 --> 01:19:39,980
I suggested that we go visit.

1531
01:19:39,980 --> 01:19:42,311
[She Bought A Tart To Go]
This is really tasty.

1532
01:19:42,311 --> 01:19:45,147
[As A Gift For The Friend]
Take a look at this pastry.

1533
01:19:45,147 --> 01:19:46,481
[Who Told Her About Café Bong Joon Ho]
See that?

1534
01:19:46,481 --> 01:19:48,817
It's so delicious.

1535
01:19:48,817 --> 01:19:50,752
- That's why you got it?
- Yes.

1536
01:19:50,752 --> 01:19:53,121
- It looks special.
- Also,

1537
01:19:53,121 --> 01:19:54,690
the scent.

1538
01:19:54,690 --> 01:19:57,926
- It's very vivid.
- The scent of the barley leaves.

1539
01:19:57,926 --> 01:19:59,861
I said to Seong Ju on my way here

1540
01:19:59,861 --> 01:20:02,497
that you'd be talking about this all week.

1541
01:20:02,497 --> 01:20:08,270
Today turned out to be healing for me.

1542
01:20:08,270 --> 01:20:11,740
My legs have been hurting lately,

1543
01:20:11,740 --> 01:20:13,942
so I felt a bit depressed.

1544
01:20:13,942 --> 01:20:16,943
I struggled a lot because of my legs.

1545
01:20:19,081 --> 01:20:22,517
It's been about two months

1546
01:20:22,517 --> 01:20:24,119
since her knee replacement.

1547
01:20:24,119 --> 01:20:27,452
[Calendar For Medicine]

1548
01:20:29,891 --> 01:20:33,829
But the café really cheered me up.

1549
01:20:33,829 --> 01:20:37,463
I was almost moved to tears by it.
